Commentary: Kemar Roach begins with a length ball, shaping away, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone. Movement straightaway for Kemar Roach!
Tad fuller now, around middle. Alex Lees shows the full face of the bat and blocks it out.
Fraction shorter now, around the fifth stump line. Alex Lees offers no shot to that.
Swinging it away, on a length, outside off, at 126 clicks. Alex Lees lets that go through to the keeper.
An outswinger once again, on a length, outside off. Alex Lees blocks it out.
Shaping away, outside off, length delivery. Alex Lees shoulders his arms to it. A maiden to begin with!
Jayden Seales starts off with a length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it watchfully.
Much fuller now, swinging away once again, outside off, at 136 clicks. Zak Crawley drives and finds the fielder at mid off.
Back of a length, hint of away movement, outside off, at 131 clicks. Zak Crawley lets that go through to the keeper.
Fuller ball, outside off, swinging away. Zak Crawley leans and dabs it towards point.
Good-length delivery, outside off, at 135 clicks. Zak Crawley does not fiddle with that.
Tad shorter, outside off, angling away. Zak Crawley leaves it alone. Another maiden!
On a length, nipping away, outside off. Alex Lees lets that go through.
Kemar Roach pulls his length back just a tad, outside off, swinging away. Alex Lees taps it towards cover.
Length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Full delivery now, around middle. Alex Lees pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Alex Lees and England are underway in style! Not the best delivery by Kemar Roach! On a length, darting it on the pads. Alex Lees flicks it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Outside off, nipping away, on a length. Alex Lees leaves it alone.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! West Indies have got an early breakthrough! Jayden Seales strikes and gets rid of Zak Crawley for a duck! This is just the start West Indies were hoping for! On a length, outside off, shaping away. Zak Crawley was in two minds, whether to leave that one or to play that and he ends up leaving his bat hanging around the off pole. The ball goes off the bottom edge towards Joshua Da Silva, who dives to his right and takes a sharp catch! Good start for West Indies!
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Fraction shorter, outside off. Joe Root lets that go through!
Another good-length delivery, swinging away, outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone.
An outswinger, wide of off, on a length. Joe Root once again offers no shot.
Beaten! Beautifully bowled! Length ball, shaping away, around the fifth stump line. Joe Root hangs back and looks to defend but he misses and the ball zips past the outside edge.
Fuller now, around off. Joe Root presses forward and defends it out watchfully. A wicket-maiden for Jayden Seales!
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Another length ball, outside off, moving away. Alex Lees lets that go through!
Another outswinger, tad fuller, at around 131 clicks, outside off.. Alex Lees once again leaves it alone.
Kemar Roach pitches this one up, swinging away, outside off. Alex Lees leans and drives it past cover for a boundary.
On a length, darting it on the pads. Alex Lees tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Fuller ball, outside off, swinging away. Joe Root drives gently past cover for a single. He gets off the mark with that.
Really well bowled! Length and on off, hint of away movement. It is defended nicely.
Drags his length back a little and bowls it on middle, defended.
FOUR! Smacked! The short ball does not trouble Root, he goes back, gets on top of the bounce, and pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
Good length and on off, Root plays it to mid off.
On the fuller side, Root shows the full face of the bat and drives it to mid off.
Fuller and on off, Root strokes it to mid on.
Nice amount of away movement but he starts it off from outside off. Left alone easily.
Better! Gets it to shape away from slightly closer to the off pole, still not close enough. Lees is beaten as he tries to block.
Continues with the line outside off, Lees does not fiddle with it.
Attacks the stumps this time, this is defended nicely.
Makes the batter play again as it is bowled on off, blocked.
A harmless maiden! Ends with a delivery well outside off, not played at.
Well bowled! Gets it to shape away from middle, Root looks to defend but does so outside the line. He gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Solid! On a length and around off, blocked.

NOT OUT! That is going well over! Always seemed the case! There is good bounce on this surface. Windies lose a review. This is on a length and around middle, it lands and holds its line. Root looks to block but it goes past the outside edge and hits the back pad. An appeal but turned down. It is a review, more because it is Root. Replays show it is going over.
Length again and on off, this is pushed to cover. Good stuff from the Windies so far.
Another one outside off, Root shoulders arms to this one.
Continues to bowl it outside off, Root does not play at it.
On middle, defended.

FOUR! Very nicely played! That will release a little bit of pressure. This is on a length and around off, Lees strokes it on the up and through mid off for a boundary. A shot that will give him confidence.
Lands this around off and gets it to move away, left alone.
Another nut not on the stumps, Lees does not play at it.
That is a good leave! Just outside off, shaping away. Lees watches it carefully and lets it go.

Just short! Roach gets it to move away from closer to the off pole. He angles it in at first and then moves it away. Lees looks to defend but does so inside the line, it goes off the outside edge but lands short of second slip.
Two! Angled into the pads, this is clipped through mid-wicket for two.
Outside off, that is an easy leave.
Yet another leave! Length and outside off, shaping away. Not played at.
Fuller in length and on off, Root pushes it to covers.
FOUR! That is a lovely shot! He opens the face of the bat at the end really nicely! Outside off, fuller, Root leans into it and drives it past point for a boundary.
Another one outside off, Root leaves it alone.
Kemar Roach delivers a length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees does not offer any shot.
Tad fuller now, swinging away, wide of off. Alex Lees once again leaves it alone.
Closer to the off pole now, on a length, shaping away, at 126 clicks. Alex Lees shoulders his arms.
Much fuller now, around middle, at 130 clicks. Alex Lees pushes it back to the bowler with the inner half of his bat.
Fullish ball again, outside off. Alex Lees leans and defends it towards cover.
Much better this time from Kemar Roach! Fractions shorter, shaping away late, outside off. Alex Lees stays in his crease and looks to block this but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, outside off. Joe Root blocks it out watchfully.
Fuller this time, outside off again. Joe Root drives it to the fielder at cover.
Fraction shorter, angling in, around middle. Joe Root defends it off the back foot.
Shaping away now, outside off, on a length. Joe Root taps it towards point.

FOUR! Edged...and over! Alzarri Joseph serves a fuller ball, outside off, swinging away. Joe Root leans to drive, but the ball goes off the outside edge over the slip cordon towards third man for a boundary!
Good-length delivery, outside off. Joe Root defends it out.
Veerasammy Permaul begins with a quicker on, outside off. Alex Lees shuffles across and blocks it out.
Turning it in, around middle. Alex Lees covers the stumps and defends it out towards the leg side.
Fuller ball, at around 84 clicks. Alex Lees blocks it out off the back foot.
Flatter ball, tad quicker, around middle. Alex Lees stays in his crease and defends it out.
Tosses it up this time, full and outside off. Alex Lees presses forward and defends this one.
Flatter again, around off. Alex Lees blocks it out solidly off the back foot. A maiden to begin with for Veerasammy Permaul!
On a length, angling away, outside off. Joe Root lets that go through to the keeper.
Tad fuller now, swinging away, outside off. Joe Root looks to have a poke at it, but the ball goes off the outside edge away from the third slip fielder.
Fuller now, spraying it down the leg side. Joe Root looks to flick but misses.
Alzarri Joseph drops it short now, around middle. Joe Root pulls it gently towards deep square leg for a single.
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away, at 141 clicks. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Another length delivery, outside off. Alex Lees defends it out towards cover. Just 1 off the over!
Veerasammy Permaul goes 'round the wicket to the right-hander, serves a fuller ball, around middle. Joe Root presses forward and defends it out.
Tosses it u again, very full again, around middle and off. Joe Root blocks it out towards the leg side.
Quicker now, around 87 clicks, darting it on the pads. Joe Root hangs back and clips it towards square leg.
Loopy delivery, around off. Joe Root lunges and blocks it out.
Flighted delivery, very full, outside off. Joe Root leans and taps it towards cover.
Full again, around middle and off. Joe Root gets down on one knee and looks to sweep this but ends up dragging with the inner half of his bat towards deep square leg for a single.
Angled into the pads, this is clipped down to fine leg for one.
Outside off, an easy leave.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, not played at.
Good length and on off, defended.
Angling away from the off pole, Lees watches it go to the keeper.
Tossed up on off, nicely bowled. Defended.
Slower through the air and lands it outside off, blocked.
Flatter this time and on off, Root stays back and guides it to point.
Slower through the air, Root waits and guides it to point. He wants one but is sent back.
Angled into middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and on middle, Lees is solid in defense. Another tidy over from Veerasammy Permaul.
Good length and on off, this is guided to point.
Just outside off, that is an easy leave.
On a length and on off, Root gets right behind the line and keeps it out.

Short and on middle, Root pulls it through square leg and takes one. This is good stuff from the Windies. They are keeping it tight and bowling that odd short one as a surprise delivery. Has not caused a lot of problems though.
Again, tidy stuff! Shorter and on off, Lees blocks.
Another delivery on a length and around off, defended.
Very full and outside off, Root looks to sweep, it goes off the underedge through square leg for one.
Slows it up and bowls it outside off, left alone.
Flatter and on off, this is defended.
Good lines and lengths! This is slowed up and it is given air, lands it outside off, blocked.
On off, blocked.
Two! Flatter and on middle, this is worked through square leg. Two taken.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
On middle, Root works it to mid-wicket.
Angled into the pads, Root looks to flick but misses.
On the stumps, defended.
Two more! Angled into the pads, Root works it fine on the leg side and takes two.

An appeal, then a discussion as the umpire does not give it out but no review. It was probably for a caught behind. Length and on off, this one jags back in. Root looks to defend, it does hit the pad but not sure about the bat and carries to the keeper. An appeal but turned down. Replays show that there is bat. Ultra Edge spots a spike. Big, big chance goes by.
Flatter and on off, defended.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
On off, this is defended nicely.
On the stumps, defended again.
Tossed up outside off, this is swept through square leg for one.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
Angles it away from the off pole. Left alone.
Another length ball, it moves away from outside off. Lees does not play at that.
Now gets this one to shape back in! It is fuller and around off, Lees pushes it to mid off.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Well timed in the end! He seemed in two minds through. Length and outside off, Lees leans forward, he just pushes it through covers for two.
On off, defended.
Tossed up on off, defended.
On middle, defended.
FOUR! Crunched! The sweep is out and Root plays that very well, he nails it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, blocked.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
Well bowled! Slows it up and lands it on middle, kept out well.
Jason Holder pitches it up, wide of off, angling away. Alex Lees watches it sail through to the keeper.
Tad fuller again, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Full in length, swinging away from the left-hander, outside off, at 126 clicks. Alex Lees offers not shot.
On a length, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Alex Lees once again, lets it go through to the keeper.
Change of angle now for Jason Holder! He goes 'round the wicket, serves a fuller ball, angling in, outside off. Alex Lees leans and blocks it towards cover.
Fuller ball, outside off. Joe Root pushes it towards mid off.
Jayden Seales pulls his length back now, outside off. Joe Root dabs it towards point.
Back of a length, outside off, shaping away, at 133 clicks. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Yorker-length delivery, on middle. Joe Root digs it out towards mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Jayden Seales drops it short now, around middle. Alex Lees ducks underneath it.
Jayden Seales ends the over with a fuller ball, outside off, swinging away. Alex Lees does not fiddle with it.
Jason Holder goes over the wicket, serves a length ball, angling in, around middle. Joe Root defends it out.
Another length delivery, outside off, gets this one to shape away. Joe Root offers no shot.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Joe Root blocks it out watchfully.
Length again, outside off. Joe Root leans and leaves it alone.
Well bowled! Better line from Jason Holder! On a length again, this one comes back in, around the fifth stump. Joe Root looks to play this but bails out initially and lets that go through.
Much fuller now, around middle. Joe Root pushes it towards mid on. A maiden for Jason!
Tad shorter, shaping away, outside off. Alex Lees looks to have a poke at it but gets beaten.
On a length, shaping away, at 137 clicks, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Angling in, on the pads. Alex Lees looks to flick, but he misses and gets rapped on the pads.
Jayden Seales drops it short now, around middle. Alex Lees ducks and lets that go through to the keeper.
Angling in, down the leg side this time. Alex Lees looks to tuck this away, but he misses.
Very full this time, around middle and off. Alex Lees drives it towards mid off. Back-to-back maidens for West Indies!
Angling in, on a length, around middle. Joe Root works it away through square leg for a single.

Change of angle for Kemar Roach! He goes 'round the wicket to the left-hander, delivers a length ball, around middle and off. Alex Lees looks to push this one but gets an inside edge back onto his pads.
Fuller this time, outside off. Alex Lees drives and finds the fielder at extra cover.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Angling in around middle and off, on a length. Alex Lees blocks it out off the back foot.
Fuller and wide of off this time. Alex Lees leans and drives this but finds the fielder at cover. Just 1 run off the last 3 overs for England.
Fuller ball, angling in around middle. Joe Root clips it past square leg and rotates the strike.
Back of a length, outside off, at 134 clicks. Alex Lees does not fiddle with it.
Shorter again, shaping away, outside off. Alex Lees hangs back and pushes it towards cover.
Another short ball, outside off. Alex Lees punches it off the back foot towards cover-point.
Jayden Seales pitches it up this time, around off. Alex Lees pushes it towards mid off.
Jayden Seales ends the over with a shorter ball, around middle. Alex Lees ducks under it and lets that go through.
On a length, angling in, around middle. Joe Root presents the full face of his bat and defends it out.
Another length delivery, jags back in, around middle, at 134 clicks. Joe Root defends it out solidly.
Fuller this time, outside off, at 135 clicks. Joe Root presses forward and blocks it out.
On a length, nipping back in, on the pads. Joe Root flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Outside off, on a length. Alex Lees watches it sail through to the keeper.
Length delivery, angling in, around middle. Alex Lees looks to tuck this away on the leg side, but he misses and gets rapped on his thigh pads. That will be Lunch on Day 1!
Jason Holder starts with a fuller ball, angling in, around middle and leg. Joe Root flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
On a length this time, coming back in around middle. Alex Lees blocks it out watchfully.
Tad fuller now, around middle. Alex Lees pushes it back to the bowler with the inner half of his bat.
Jason Holder once again pitches it up, outside off. Alex Lees pushes it gently past mid off for a couple of runs. 50 up for England!
Length delivery this time, around middle, at 127 clicks. Alex Lees defends it out.
Holder ends the over with a short delivery, around middle. Alex Lees ducks underneath it.
On a length, outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Swings away, on a length, outside off. Joe Root once again lets that go through.
Fuller now, angling in around middle. Joe Root blocks it out off the front foot.
Another length delivery, outside off. Joe Root stays in his crease and dabs it towards point.
Fuller ball, coming back in around middle. Joe Root defends it out solidly.
Kemar Roach pitches it up again, outside off. Joe Root presses forward and drives it past cover for a couple of runs.
Jason Holder goes 'round the wicket, delivers a length ball, outside off. Alex Lees cuts it to point.
Back of a length, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
This one nips back in, on a length, around off. Alex Lees looks to defend but he manages to get an inside edge back onto his pads.
Another length delivery, around off. Alex Lees blocks it out watchfully.
Tad fuller, angling in around middle. Alex Lees flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Length, outside off. Alex Lees lets it go through to the keeper.

DROPPED! A chance goes down! On a length, angling in, down the leg side. Joe Root flicks and gets a tickle back to the keeper. Joshua Da Silva dives to his right, gets his glove on it but fails to grab it. Kemar Roach cannot believe it! Joe Root gets a life.
On a length, outside off. Joe Root taps it towards gully.
Fuller now, attacking the stumps. Joe Root drives it towards mid on.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Joe Root hangs back and dabs it towards point.
Full now, on middle. Joe Root pushes it back to the bowler.
Angling in, around middle, on a fuller length. Joe Root tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Length, outside off. Joe Root leans and defends it out.
Tad shorter now, outside off again. Joe Root hops and taps it towards point.
Fuller ball this time, angling in around middle. Joe Root pushes it towards mid on.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Well bowled! Nipping back in sharply this time, on a length, around the fifth stump line. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Fraction shorter, outside off. Joe Root stays in his crease and dabs it towards gully.
Slightly shorter and outside off, this is guided to point.

Really well bowled! Goes for a yorker, gets it to tail back in. Lees does well to jam it out towards square leg. Surprise nut. Roach has been hitting the length area and also taking it away. This time does completely the opposite.
Good length and on middle, blocked.
Length again and on off, Lees pushes it to covers.
A yorker and on off, Lees jams it out. Really good stuff from Roach. Testing lines and lengths.

FOUR! That is not a good ball! Commentator's curse maybe! Wide and fuller outside off, this is carved through point for a boundary. Fifty run stand up! Slow going so far but it is important for the two to hang in there.
Two more! Angled into the pads, Root clips it through square leg and takes two.
Goes back to bowling it on a length and around off, defended.
On the fuller side, Root shows the full face of the bat and strokes it to mid off.
Back of a length and on off, Root guides it to point.
Good shot but for no runs! Fuller and on off, Root drives but to covers.
Angled into middle, Root strokes it to mid on.
Fuller and on off, Lees plays it to mid off.
A yorker outside off, it is jammed out to point.
On off, Lees pushes it to covers.
Another one on a length, blocked.
Well bowled! Length and around off, this lands and moves away. Lees looks to defend but then pulls his bat back.
Shorter ball now, around middle. Alex Lees ducks under it.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Fuller ball now, around middle and leg. Joe Root clips it past square leg for a boundary.
A stifled appeal for LBW, but the umpire says no! Joe Root looks to blocks this but gets an inside edge back onto the pad.
Outside off, shaping away, on a length. Joe Root taps it towards point.
Another length delivery, outside off, moving away. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off. Joe Root cuts it towards point.
Another good-length delivery, width on offer this time. Joe Root hangs back and once again chops it towards point.
Angling in, around off, on a length. Alex Lees defends it out.
Tad fuller now, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Alex Lees taps it towards cover and scampers through to the other end.
On a length, width on offer now. Joe Root hangs back and cuts it towards the fielder at gully.
FOUR! Glorious! Alzarri Joseph pitches it up again, outside off. Joe Root leans and creams it past cover for a beautiful boundary.
Wide of off again, fuller ball. Joe Root once again drives but finds the fielder at cover this time.
Full-length delivery, outside off. Alex Lees presses forward and drives it to the fielder at short cover.
On a length now, around middle, at 133 clicks. Alex Lees hangs back and blocks it out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Alex Lees closes the face of his bat and pushes it past mid off. Two taken!
Wide of off this time, full in length. Alex Lees drives it to the fielder at cover.
This one lands on a length, outside off, at 136 clicks. Alex Lees defends it out solidly.
Shorter ball, arounnd middle. Alex Lees ducks, but the ball hits him on the helmet.
Shorter ball, down the leg side. Joe Root pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
Another shorter ball, down the leg side. Alex Lees pulls it towards deep square leg and rotates the strike.
Alzarri Joseph bangs in short again, around middle and off. Joe Root pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
On a length, angling in around middle and leg. Alex Lees tucks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Shorter ball, outside off. Alex Lees stands tall and taps it towards point.
Alzarri Joseph drops it short again, down the leg side, at 135 clicks. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off, at 134 clicks. Joe Root leans and leaves it alone.
Shaping away just a tad, outside off, another length delivery. Joe Root does not fiddle with it.
Angling in, fuller in length, on the pads. Joe Root clips it towards deep mid-wicket. Single taken!
Good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off, at 130 clicks. Alex Lees shoulders his arms at it.
Very full on this occasion, outside off. Alex Lees leans and pushes it toward the fielder at silly mid off.
Shorter this time, around middle. Alex Lees pulls it towards deep mid-wicket and runs across to the other end. He retains the strike!
Back of a length, shaping away, outside off. Alex Lees stays back and taps it towards the fielder at gully, who collects the ball on the bounce.
Another shorter ball, outside off again. Alex Lees pushes it off the back foot past point for a single.
Back of a length, around middle. Joe Root pulls it to fine leg and rotates the strike.
On a length this time, outside off. Alex Lees leans and defends it out solidly.
On a length, outside off. Alex Lees stays in his crease and taps it towards point.
Outside off, on a good length. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Loopy ball, outside off, fuller ball. Joe Root pushes it towards cover.
Full again, outside off. Joe Root defends it out.
Tosses it up, slower through the air,  outside off, full in length. Joe Root leans and defends it out.
Another fuller ball, on the pads this time. Joe Root defends it out.
Shorter ball now, outside off. Joe Root pushes it towards cover for a single. That will be fifty for Joe Root! It's been another fine innings! He has kicked up right where he left off from!

OUT! LBW! Veerasammy Permaul comes back into the attack and strikes straightaway! West Indies have finally broken this partnership! A fuller ball, turning it in, on middle. Alex Lees hangs back and looks to flick this but he misses as the ball spins in. He gets rapped on the pads, and the umpire raises his finger after an appeal for LBW. Alex Lees does not take the review, and he walks back. Dan Lawrence is the new man in.
Howout: lbw b Veerasammy Permaul

Commentary: Back of a length, outside off. Joe Root hangs back and punches it towards cover.
Another shorter ball, angling in, around middle. Joe Root flicks it towards square leg and scampers through to the other end.
On a length, around middle. Dan Lawrence blocks it out.
Outside off, on a length. Dan Lawrence stays in his crease and cuts it towards point. Jermaine Blackwood there dives to his left and makes a good stop!
Fuller now, outside off. Dan Lawrence drives it towards mid off. No run there!
Another fuller ball, angling in on middle. Dan Lawrence pushes it towards mid on.
Loopy ball, very full, on middle. Joe Root leans defends it out
Slower through the air again, full, outside off. Joe Root drives and pushes it towards cover for a single.
Fuller ball at around 84 clicks, on middle. Dan Lawrence leans and pushes it towards mid on.
Turning it away, fuller ball, around off. Dan Lawrence stays back and pushes it to the fielder at cover.
Tad quicker now, spinning away, outside off. Dan Lawrence once again pushes it to cover off the back foot.
Full now, on middle. Dan Lawrence skips down the pitch and knocks it towards mid on.
Very full, angling in, around middle. Joe Root clips it past mid on for a brace.
On a length this time, nipping back in, around middle, at 138 clicks. Joe Root defends it out off the back foot.
Another length delivery, outside off, at 136 clicks. Joe Root hangs back and cuts it towards the fielder at gully who collects the ball on the bounce.
Another length delivery, outside off. Joe Root defends it towards cover.
Jayden Seales drops it short now, around off. Joe Root pulls it through square leg for a single.
Fraction short again, on middle. Dan Lawrence presents the full face of the bat and blocks it out.
FOUR! Perfection execution! He loves playing the sweep shot! A fuller ball, down leg. Joe Root gets down on his knee and sweeps it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Fuller ball again, slower through the air, on middle. Joe Root sweeps once again but finds the fielder at square leg. Two taken!
Loopy ball, outside off, full again. Joe Root leans and defends it out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Joe Root dabs it towards point.
Tosses it up, full, on middle. Joe Root leans an defends it out.
Full again, on middle. Joe Root eases it down to long on for a single. He retains the strike.
On a length, down the leg side. Joe Root tries to flick this but misses.
On a length again, nipping back in, around middle. Joe Root tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller this time, outside off, hint of away movement. Joe Root taps it towards backward point.
Much fuller now angling in on the pads. Joe Root flicks it past square leg for a brace.
On a length this time, around middle. Joe Root blocks it out watchfully.
Pitches it up, on the pads. Joe Root flicks it to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery, full, on middle. Dan Lawrence has blocked this off the front foot.
Loopy ball, full again, on middle. Dan Lawrence once again leans and defends it out.
Turning away, outside off, fullish ball. Dan Lawrence hangs back and cuts it past point for a brace. He gets off the mark with that!
Fuller ball, tosses it up, on middle. Dan Lawrence presses forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Another loopy ball, full, on middle. Dan Lawrence blocks it out off the front foot.
Slower through the air, pitches it up, around middle and leg. Dan Lawrence flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Exquisite timing on that! Jason Holder overpitches this one, on middle. Dan Lawrence presents the full face of the bat and drives it straight down the ground for a boundary. 100 up for England!
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Another solid stroke from Dan Lawrence. Another full delivery, on the pads this time. Dan Lawrence uses his wrists and flicks it wide of mid on for another boundary.
Better from Jason Holder! On a length, outside off. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.

Quick single! On a length, around middle. Dan Lawrence taps it on the right of the mid on fielder and scampers through to the other end. John Campbell runs towards the ball, tries to collect the ball with his right hand but fails to do so cleanly. Dan Lawrence dives to make his ground. There was no need to run for that!
Shorter ball, outside off. Joe Root taps it towards gully.
Another length ball, shaping away, outside off. Joe Root dabs it towards gully once again.
Loopy ball, full, around middle and off. Dan Lawrence leans and defends it out.
Full again, around middle. Dan Lawrence knocks it to long on for a single.
Slower through the air, full again, on middle. Joe Root defends it out.
Flighted delivery, full, outside off. Joe Root leans and drives it towards cover.
Loopy ball, full, around off. Joe Root strokes it towards cover.
Tosses it up, outside off. Joe Root taps it towards point.
On a length, around middle. Dan Lawrence taps it towards the fielder at silly mid on, who fails to stop the ball, which allows the batters to sneak in a run.
fuller now, around middle. Joe Root pushes it back to the bowler. Jason Holder collects the ball and throws it towards the striker's end. A little bit of frustration shown by Jason Holder there!
On a length, around middle. Joe Root works it away towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller now, outside off. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
Full again, wide of off. Dan Lawrence drives it back to the bowler.
Pitches it up again, outside off. Dan Lawrence taps it towards cover.
FOUR! Once again the sweep shot! Loopy ball full, around middle. Joe Root gets low brings out his broom and sweeps it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary!
Outside off, full again. Joe Root taps it towards point.
Quicker now, sliding it on middle. Joe Root flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
SIX! BANG! Fuller ball, around middle. Dan Lawrence shimmies down the pitch and tonks it towards over deep mid-wicket for a biggie.
Edged and just short! Loopy ball, fuller, outside off. Dan Lawrence leans to block this but the ball goes off the outside edge and falls just short of the fielder at first slip.
Full again, loopy ball, around middle. Dan Lawrence leans and taps it in front of the short leg fielder who stops the ball on the bounce.
On a length, outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Very full again, around off. Joe Root shuffles across and taps it towards mid on.
Pitches it up again, down the leg side now. Joe Root looks to flick but he misses.
Jason Holder drops it short now, around middle. Joe Root pulls it towards fine leg for a brace.
FOUR! Nicely done! On a length now, outside off. Joe Root waits for it, opens the face of the bat and guides it past gully, towards third man for a boundary.
Tad slower, on a length, around off. Joe Root blocks it out.
Tosses it up, outside off, on a fuller length. Dan Lawrence leans and blocks it out.
Another loopy delivery, full, on middle. Dan Lawrence presses forward and defends this one.
FOUR! Veerasammy Permaul drops this short and wide of off. Dan Lawrence accepts this gift. He waits for it and slashes it past point for a boundary. That brings up the 50-run stand between these two!
Fuller now, around middle. Dan Lawrence steps down and eases it down to long on for a single.
Fuller ball, on middle. Joe Root defends it out.
Full again, around middle. Joe Root pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Shorter ball, spinning away, around off. Joe Root defends this one.
Fuller this time, outside off. Joe Root cuts it towards point.
Full length, on middle. John Campbell blocks it from within the crease.
Loopy ball, full and on off. Joe Root eases it towards long off for a single.
Shorter ball, on middle. Dan Lawrence hangs back and works it away through square leg for a single.
Tosses it up, very full, outside off. Joe Root drives it past cover for a single. He retains the strike!
Shorter ball, spinning away, around off. Joe Root punches it past cover for a single.
Fuller ball, around middle. Dan Lawrence leans and defends it out.
Flatter ball, on middle. Dan Lawrence works it away towards mid-wicket.
Tosses it up, on middle. Dan Lawrence pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller now, flighted ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence leans and defends it towards cover.
Veerasammy Permaul ends the over with a fuller ball, on middle. Dan Lawrence defends it out. That will be Team on Day 1!
Fuller ball, outside off. Joe Root drives it to the fielder at mid off.
Back of a length, around middle. Joe Root pulls it towards square leg for a single.
On a length, around middle. Dan Lawrence pushes it towards mid on.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Dan Lawrence shuffles across and defends it back to the bowler.
Quick single! Another length delivery, outside off. Dan Lawrence taps it towards cover and scampers through to the other end.
Angling in around middle, on a length. Joe Root taps it towards mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, full, on middle. Dan Lawrence presses forward and defends it out.
Short this time, outside off, turning away. Dan Lawrence cuts it towards the fielder at point.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Shorter ball, spinning away, outside off. Dan Lawrence waits in the crease and cuts it late past gully for a boundary.
Loopy ball this time, full, on middle. Dan Lawrence lunges and defends it out.
Veerasammy Permaul drops his length back now, around middle. Dan Lawrence hangs back and pushes it towards square leg for a single.
Loopy ball, full, outside off. Joe Root leans and pushes it towards cover for a single.
On a length, around middle. Joe Root pushes it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Edgy runs! Another length delivery, outside off. Joe Root looks to cut this away, but the ball goes off the outside edge between the keeper and the first slip fielder towards third man for a boundary.
Shorter ball, outside off. Joe Root pushes it towards cover.
Fuller now, outside off. Joe Root defends it out.
Full, angling in, around middle. Joe Root flicks it past mid-wicket for a single.

Mix-up....but no harm done! Fuller ball, around middle. Dan Lawrence taps it towards mid off and he leaves his crease. Joe Root is still waiting at his end. A midfield at mid off, allows Joe Root to comfortably reach the other end. Single at the end.
Shorter ball, wide of off. Dan Lawrence slashes it past cover for a brace.
Fuller ball, around middle. Dan Lawrence knocks it down to long on for a single.
Loopy ball, on middle. Joe Root lunges forward and blocks it out.
Spinning away, tad shorter, around middle. Joe Root pushes it back to the bowler off the back foot.
Loopy ball, full, down leg. Joe Root looks to sweep but he misses.
Fuller ball, around middle. Joe Root defends it out.
FOUR! Classy! What a shot! Full, wide of off. Dan Lawrence presses forward and drives it past cover for a gorgeous boundary.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Dan Lawrence is enjoying himself out there. A length ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence hangs back and steers past gully for another boundary. Alzarri Joseph over overstepped here and a no ball is called!
A low full toss, on the pads. Dan Lawrence drives it to the fielder at mid on. Another no ball, as Alzarri Joseph once again has over stepped!
Alzarri Joseph drops it short now, outside off. Dan Lawrence ducks underneath it.
Fraction shorter now, down the leg side. Dan Lawrence tucks it through square leg for a single.
Shorter ball, outside off. Joe Root pulls it towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Fantastic shot! Another shorter ball, around middle. Dan Lawrence picks up the length, swivels, and pulls it towards deep square leg for a boundary. He moves to 49 with that!
Alzarri Joseph drops it short once again, around middle. Dan Lawrence this time ducks under it.
Shorter ball, outside off. Joe Root cuts it to point.
Fuller now, outside off, drifting in. Joe Root blocks it out.
Loopy ball, full, around off. Joe Root defends it out.
Shorter ball, on middle. Joe Root blocks it out off the back foot.
Shorter ball, angling in, around middle. Joe Root flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Spinning away, outside off. Dan Lawrence hangs back and looks to cut this away, but he misses.
Shorter ball, around middle. Joe Root miscues his pull shot towards square leg.
FOUR! He gets hold of it this time! Another shorter ball, down the leg side. Joe Root swivels and pulls it towards fine leg for a boundary. He moves to 93 with that!
Down the leg side, shorter ball. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around middle. Joe Root once again pulls and finds the fielder at deep square leg. Single taken!
Very short on this occasion, around middle. Dan Lawrence ducks underneath it.
Back of a length, around middle and off. Dan Lawrence defends it out solidly.
Loopy ball, full, slower through the air, outside off. Joe Root leans and pushes it towards cover for a single. He moves to 95 with that run!
Shorter ball, around middle. Dan Lawrence defends it out off the back foot.

Bye! Down the leg side, fuller ball. Dan Lawrence looks to flick this, but he fails to get any bat on it. Joshua Da Silva too fails to grab the ball and it rolls towards fine leg. The batters steal in a bye!
Very full, around the leg pole, slower through the air. Joe Root works it away towards fine leg for a brace.

Bye! Down the leg side, fuller ball. Dan Lawrence looks to flick this, but he fails to get any bat on it. Joshua Da Silva too fails to grab the ball and it rolls towards fine leg. The batters steal in a bye!
Shorter ball, outside off. Joe Root punches it past cover for a brace. He moves to 99 now! That brings up the 100-run stand between these two!
Shorter ball, down the leg side. Dan Lawrence pulls it towards fine leg for a single. 50 for Dan Lawrence! He has looks exceptional so far! That is his fasted fifty in Test matches!

There it is! A shorter ball, around middle. Joe Root pulls it towards deep square leg for a single. That will be 100 for Joe Root! He just cannot stop scoring runs. Back-to-back centuries for him. That is his 25th Test hundred! It's been another masterclass innings from the England Skipper. Off comes his helmet, and Dan Lawrence walks across to hug him!
Short again, around middle. Dan Lawrence swivels and pulls it through square leg for a single
Another shorter ball, around middle and leg. Joe Root looks to pull this but he gets a bottom edge onto the deck.
Jayden Seales maintains the same length, drops it short again, around middle. Joe Root swivels and pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
Very short now, around middle and leg. Dan Lawrence ducks underneath it and lets it go.
Fuller ball, wide of off. Joe Root presses forward and drives it past cover for a boundary.
Angling in, on a length, outside off. Dan Lawrence leans and blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Dan Lawrence once again blocks it out solidly.
Much fuller now, outside off. Dan Lawrence leans and drives it to the fielder at cover.
On a length, outside off. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Dan Lawrence stays in his crease and chops it towards third man for a single.
Jayden Seales continues to bowl short delivery, around middle. Joe Root swivels and pulls it towards deep square and rotates the strike.
Fraction short again, outside off. Dan Lawrence hops and defends it towards cover.
Wide! Very short on this occasion, down leg. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone and wide is called for height!
Down the leg side now, short ball. Dan Lawrence pulls it towards square leg for a single.
Back of a length, on the bodyline. Joe Root swivels and pulls it towards deep square leg yet another single.
Outside off this time, another shorter ball. Dan Lawrence shuffles across and pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Down the leg side, another short ball. Joe Root pulls and finds the fielder at square leg this time.
Full in length, outside off. Dan Lawrence lunges and defends it out.
Another fuller ball, around middle and off. Dan Lawrence punches it back to the bowler.
Pitches it up, outside off. Dan Lawrence presses forward and defends it out.
On a length this time, angling in, outside off. Dan Lawrence dabs it towards point.
Good-length delivery, around off. Dan Lawrence shuffles across and pushes it towards mid on.
On a length, around middle. Dan Lawrence blocks it out solidly.
Kraigg Brathwaite begins with a loopy ball, very full, around the leg pole. Joe Root works it away towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Tad shorter, around off. Dan Lawrence hangs back and punches it past cover for a boundary. 200 comes up for England!
Loopy ball, full, on middle. Dan Lawrence defends it out.
Slower through the air, on middle. Dan Lawrence works it away towards mid-wicket.
Tosses it up, full again, on middle. Dan Lawrence pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery, full in length. Dan Lawrence has defended this off the front foot.
Back of a length, outside off. Joe Root taps it towards point.
Back of a length, outside off. Joe Root pushes it towards point.
Angling in, on a length, around middle. Joe Root flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Much fuller this time, shaping it in, around off. Joe Root drives and finds the fielder at mid off.
Angling in again, pitches it up, around middle. Joe Root pushes it with the inner half of his bat towards mid on.
Back of a length, outside off. Joe Root taps it towards point. A maiden over!
Slower through the air, full, around middle. Dan Lawrence eases it down to long on for a single.
Fuller ball, around middle. Joe Root reverse-sweeps it past point for a single.
Tosses it up, full again, around middle and leg. Dan Lawrence works it away towards mid-wicket.
Another flighted delivery, on middle. Dan Lawrence leans and defends it out solidly.
Floated delivery, full, down the leg side. Dan Lawrence taps it towards square leg.
Shorter ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence hangs back and steers it towards third man for a brace.
Jason Holder serves a fuller ball, angling in, around middle and leg. Joe Root taps it towards mid-wicket.
On a length, angling in, on middle. Joe Root blocks it out solidly.
Yorker-length delivery, around the off pole. Joe Root digs it out.
Shorter ball now, down leg. Joe Root pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
Edged and just short! Fuller now ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence leans and looks to drive, but the ball goes off the outside edge and falls just short of Alzarri Joseph at first slip.
Jason Holder pitches it up again, outside off. Dan Lawrence pushes it back to the mid off.
Fuller ball, tosses it up, on middle. Joe Root defends it out.
Flighted delivery, full again, on middle. Joe Root blocks it out solidly.
Loopy ball, outside off. Joe Root blocks it out.
FOUR! Wow! He has made that look so easy! Fuller ball, around middle. Joe Root gets down on his knee and rever-sweeps it past point for a boundary.
Shorter now, around middle. Joe Root nudges it past mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller now, flighted, around middle. Dan Lawrence works it away towards square leg for a single.
Shorter ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence walks across and dabs it towards gully.
FOUR! Classy from Dan Lawrence! Tad fuller, wide of off. Dan Lawrence presses forward and drives it past cover for a boundary.
Fuller again, ouside off. Dan Lawrence walks across and works it away towards mid-wicket.
On a length, outside off. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
Tad fuller now, outside off. Dan Lawrence drives and finds the fielder at mid off.
Angling in, on middle, on a length. Dan Lawrence knocks it mid on.
Fuller ball, tosses it up, on middle. Joe Root defends it out.
Quicker now, down the leg side, fuller ball. Joe Root taps it back to the bowler.
Slower now, full, down the leg side. Joe Root sweeps it towards fine leg for a single.
Flighted delivery, full, on off. Dan Lawrence has blocked this one.
Quicker, flatter, outside off. Dan Lawrence dabs it towards point.
Fuller now, tosses it up, around middle. Dan Lawrence nudges it towards mid-wicket.
A length ball, angling in around middle. Dan Lawrence works it towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Another length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
Tad fuller, angling in, around middle, at 126 clicks. Dan Lawrence clips it towards mid on.
On a length, outside off. Dan Lawrence opens the face of the bat and guides it towards cover-point for a single.
Nipping back in a tad, on a length, around middle. Joe Root defends it out solidly.
Outside off, on a length. Joe Root dabs it towards point.
Loopy ball, full, around middle. Dan Lawrence pushes it towards mid on.
Tosses it up, very full, around middle and leg. Dan Lawrence looks to tuck this away, but he misses.
Fuller ball, on middle. Dan Lawrence leans and defends it out.
Angling down the leg side, fuller ball. Dan Lawrence looks to flick but he gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Flighted delivery, full, on middle. Dan Lawrence lunges and blocks it out.
Full, on the leg stump. Dan Lawrence clips it towards square leg for a single.
Jayden Seales delivers it on a length, angling in, on middle. Dan Lawrence drives it to mid on.
Fuller now, outside off. Dan Lawrence pushes it to cover-point. Single taken!
A low full toss, outside off. Joe Root drives and finds the fielder at cover.
Nipping back in, around middle, full again. Joe Root pushes it back to the bowler!

Mix-up...but no harm done! Another length ball, outside off. Joe Root taps it towards cover. Dan Lawrence leaves his create for a run but he is sent back mid-way. There was a throw at the bowler's end but he misses. A direct hit would have been curtains for Dan Lawrence!
Shorter ball, outside off. Joe Root cuts it towards point.
Short ball, spinning away, outside off. Dan Lawrence chops it towards the fielder at backward point.
Fuller ball, on middle. Dan Lawrence pushes it back to the bowler.
Loopy all, full, on middle. Dan Lawrence defends it out solidly.
Tosses it up again, full in length, on middle. Dan Lawrence blocks it out.
Flighted delivery, full, around off. Dan Lawrence pushes it back to the bowler.
Slower through the air, full, around middle. Dan Lawrence steps down and eases it down to long off for a single.
Angling in, on a length, around middle. Dan Lawrence defends it out.
Another length delivery, angling in, around middle. Dan Lawrence pushes it towards mid on.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Dan Lawrence defends it off the back foot.
Fraction shorter, outside off, at 127 clicks. Dan Lawrence blocks it towards cover.
Very full, on middle. Dan Lawrence digs it out.

DROPPED AND FOUR! Oh, dear! This was the last thing West Indies needed! A length ball, shaping away just a tad, outside off. Dan Lawrence leans to drive, but the ball goes off the outside edge towards Alzarri Joseph at first slip. Alzarri Joseph gets his hands to it, and he spills it out and it goes towards third man for a boundary. Jayden Seales is furious!
Outside off, fuller ball. Joe Root dabs it towards point.
Flighted delivery, full, on middle. Joe Root defends it out.
Flatter and quicker, outside off, fuller ball. Joe Root pushes it towards point for a single.
Very full, on middle. Dan Lawrence steps down and pushes it back to the bowler.
Tosses it up again, on middle, full again. Dan Lawrence blocks it out.
Very full now, outside off. Dan Lawrence pushes it back to the bowler.
Angling in on a length, around middle. Joe Root blocks it out solidly.
Shorter ball, wide of off. Joe Root chops it towards point for a single.
Another back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Dan Lawrence dabs it towards point and rotates the strike!
Swing and a miss! On a length, outside off. Joe Root hangs back and looks to cut this away but he misses.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Joe Root blocks it out off the back foot.
Length ball, angling in, outside off. Joe Root blocks it out off the front foot this time.
Pitches it up, outside off. Dan Lawrence blocks it out watchfully.
Tad shorter now, angling away, outside off. Dan Lawrence stands tall and taps it towards cover.
On a length now, shaping away, outside off. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
Swinging away again, on a length, on middle, at 123 clicks. Dan Lawrence pushes it towards mid on.
Length ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence lets that go through.
FOUR! Beautiful! Fuller ball, shaping away outside off. Dan Lawrence presses forward and drives it past mid off for a glorious boundary. That brings up the 150-run stand between these two!
Nipping back in, on a fuller length, on the pads. Joe Root flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
A good-length delivery, angling in, around middle. Dan Lawrence tucks it to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Fuller ball now, outside off. Dan Lawrence leans and leaves it alone.
Another fuller ball, outside off, at 132 clicks. Dan Lawrence drives it towards mid off.
On a length now, angling in, around middle. Dan Lawrence defends it out.
Pitches this one up, around middle. Dan Lawrence pushes it towards mid on.
On a length, nipping back in, around middle. Joe Root looks to block this bu he gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On a length, outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Another length ball, shaping away, outside off. Joe Root shoulders his arms.
Fuller this time, outside off. Joe Root leans and taps it towards cover.
Tad fuller now, outside off. Joe Root hangs back and pushes it towards backward point for a single.
Fuller ball again, angling in on the pads. Dan Lawrence works it away towards deep square leg for a single. He now moves to 82, which is his highest Test score.
On a length, outside off, at 136 clicks. Dan Lawrence punches it towards mid on.
Fuller now, outside off. Dan Lawrence leans and drives it towards cover.
Another full ball, outside off, at 131 clicks. Dan Lawrence pushes it towards cover.
Length delivery, angling away, outside off. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
Angling in, on a length, around the pads. Dan Lawrence tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Shorter ball, outside off. Joe Root dabs it towards point.
Swinging away, outside off, on a length. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, around off, at 124 clicks. Dan Lawrence blocks it out.
FOUR! Top shot! Jason Holder overpitches it, outside off. Dan Lawrence presses forward and creams it through cover for a boundary!
FOUR! back-to-back boundaries! Full again, outside off. Dan Lawrence leans and drives it past mid off for a boundary. He moves to 91 with that!

OUT! CAUGHT! Oh, dear! Disappointment for Dan Lawrence but Jason Holder is sure happy! He punches the air in delight. But it's been an exceptional innings from Dan Lawrence, he missed out on a well-deserved century here. Jason Holder delivers this on a length, shaping away, outside off. Dan Lawrence leans in and drives it towards cover, but he does so with the outer half of his bat and the ball lobs up and goes straight to Kraigg Brathwaite at cover, who pouches it safely. That will be Stumps on Day 1!
Howout: c Kraigg Brathwaite b Jason Holder

Commentary: Holder bowls the final ball of his incomplete over and it's a full and wide one. Stokes lets it through to the keeper.
Seales starts off with a loosener and spills it well wide the off stump. Joe Root shoulders arms.
Full and wide again, a bit too wide to entice Root into playing the drive. Left alone.
Better! Pitched up, around the sixth stump line and shaping away just a bit. Root makes an easy leave.
First run of the morning for England. Around off, Root presses forward and bunts it out towards cover-point for a single.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Stokes hangs back to defend it out.
Around the top of off, defended towards covers.
On a good length, around off. Root hops back and pushes it out towards covers for an easy single.
Pitched up on middle. Stokes makes a watchful block.
Fullish delivery on off stump. This is blocked towards silly mid off.
Half an appeal from Holder, nothing more. Length ball around leg stump. Stokes walks towards the ball trying to turn it leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Around middle and leg. Blocked.
On a good length, slanted across the left-hander. Ben Stokes hangs back and taps it to cover-point.
Full and hugging the tramline. Root isn't going to play at that one.
Bit of a flashy shot from Joe Root. Good-length, there's width on offer and Root looks to slap it through point. There's a bit of extra bounce and the ball zips past the outside edge of Root's blade.
Short and wide, tapped off the back foot to deep point for a single.
Full and on off, just shaping in a bit. Stokes pushes it towards short cover.
FOUR! Sumptuous from Ben Stokes and he is off the mark in style! Overpitched on middle, Stokes drives it right back past the bowler and picks up a boundary.
Very full, outside off and nipping away a bit. Stokes leaves it alone.
Around off, Root leans in and just pushes the ball in the gap at extra cover. He picks up another single.
A length ball on middle. Stokes stands tall and defends it on the leg side.
Stokes goes deep in his crease and shuffles a bit as well. Holder slants it across off and Stokes keeps it out towards cover.
Nicely bowled! A touch fuller, in that channel around off and Stokes makes a good leave.
This time Ben Stokes trying to put off Jason Holder. This is on off, Stokes pushes it towards mid on.
Length again, on off. Stokes pushes at it with soft hands and edges it down towards gully.

NOT OUT! There were two problems with the review, it was a question of whether it did hit the pad first and if it did, then was the impact in line or not. The first condition was satisfied but the latter wasn't. Fullish delivery, around off and nipping back in sharply. Joe Root presses forward looking to make the block but gets rapped on the pads. It is reviewed and the replay shows that it is pad first but Ball Tracker confirms that the impact is outside off.
Angled into middle. Root keeps it out.
Good leave. Length, close to the off stump and Root leaves it on line.
Pitched up, around off. Root pushes it out on the off side.
This is very full, on middle, almost a yorker. Root does well to jam it out.
Outside off and this is driven down to deep point for a run.
On off stump, Root gets right behind the line of the ball to block.
A length ball, on the fifth stump line. Root makes a watchful leave.
Good-length, over off. Root hops back and defends it to cover.
Full and around off. Root nudges it towards cover-point for a single. It's been a tentative start to the day from England and Joe Root has just looked to get a single every over.
Length again, on middle. Stokes defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length and close to the off pole. Stokes leaves it alone and the ball dies on its way to Joshua Da Silva behind the sticks.
Kemar Roach steams in and delivers a peach of a delivery first up. Length, angled in from outside off. The ball just holds its line at the moment and Root is beaten past the outside edge.
A touch fuller, slanting into middle from outside off. Joe Root makes a solid block.
Full and outside off, driven without much timing towards covers.
Length this time, on off. Root looks to cover drive but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards mid-wicket. The batters sneak in a run as well.
Roach comes in from 'round the wicket and bangs it in short. Stokes pulls it along the ground to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, Root looks to have a poke but pulls out and lets it through to the keeper..
A length ball, around leg. Stokes blocks it out.
Fuller in length, around off. Stokes pushes it out to cover-point.
This is a bit wider of off stump and Stokes makes an easy leave.
A low dipping full toss on middle. Ben Stokes punches it out towards mid on.
Good running! Full and straight, pushed towards wide mid on and the batters set off for a quick single.
Back of a length, around off. Root defends it off the back foot towards point.
FOUR! This is well wide of off stump. Ben Stokes rocks back and thumps it through the point region for a boundary.
Nicely bowled! Pitched up, close to the off stump and this one holds its line. Stokes makes a watchful leave.
Length again, angling in from around off.  Ben Stokes shuffles a bit and looks to work it on the leg side. He misses and gets hit high on the pads.
FOUR! A watchful start in the first half an hour is doing a world of good for Ben Stokes. A half volley, outside off and this is gloriously driven through the cover region for another boundary.
This is angled into off stump. Stokes blocks it out.
Full and around off. This is nudged onto the off side.
Fullish delivery, around off and shaping away. Root watchfully keeps it out towards the slip cordon.
Drop and run! Around the top of off, bunted out towards covers for a single.
Pitched up around off and angling away. Stokes shoulders arms to it.
On off, defended out.
Pitched up, a bit further outside off and the ball zips through to the keeper as Stokes leaves it alone.
LEG BYE! On the pads, Stokes looks to flicks but misses and the ball goes off the pads towards square leg. They scamper through for a leg bye.
A full ball, way outside off. Stokes shuffles across and lets it through.
Full ball, outside off and slightly shaping away as well. Stokes leans and drives it to deep cover for a single.
FOUR! More runs coming now! Roach angles it on the pads. Root flicks it nicely and to fine leg for a boundary.
Again on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Touch fuller and outside off. Stokes comes behind the line of the ball to block it.
Full, outside off and angling away. Left alone.
Short of a length, outside off. Root leaves it alone.
Much better! On a length, at 132 kph, on off. Root dead bats it.
Slightly full and on off. Root on drives it to mid on.
Leg bye! Length ball, angling on the pads. Root misses his tuck and gets hit on the pads. A leg bye taken as it rolls to square leg.
FOUR! Loose delivery! This is very full and well wide. Stokes frees his arms and smashes it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball, again well outside off. This time Stokes punches off the back foot through point for a couple of runs.
Full and slanting down the leg side. Worked to deep square leg for one.
On a length, around off. Stokes defends it.
A length ball, outside off, a late outward movement. Stokes prods and shoulders arms.
Beautiful bowling! Stokes is shuffling across and this time Stokes puts a full ball, on his pads. Stokes misses his whip and gets hit on the pads.
Fuller and on middle. Stokes is a touch late as he nudges it off the inside edge to square leg. A single taken.
Short in length, on middle. Root pulls it softly to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A length ball, angling around off. Root hangs back to defend.
Touch fuller and around middle. Root hits it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Length ball, around the 5th stump channel. Stokes keeps it out.
Length ball, outside off. Stokes shoulders arms to it.
A length ball, outside off. Stokes is in two minds, to leave or to play. He plays without much authority and the ball goes off the bottom part of the blade to the slip cordon.
Good end to the over from Alzarri Joseph! Another angler outside off. Stokes looks to defend with soft hands but gets an inside edge, through his legs on the leg side.
Full and on middle, drilled to long on for a single.
Flatter and spinning around off. Stokes has his stumps covered.
Tossed up, outside off. Stokes reaches to the pitch of the ball to block it out.
Flatter and on middle, flicked on the leg side.
Slower this time, on middle. Stokes leans and defends it.
Tossed up, on middle. Stokes skips down and eases it to long on for a run.
Outside off, on a length. Stokes works it to covers.
Length and on middle. Stokes bunts it to mid on.
FOUR! 'Catch it' is the call but the ball goes well over mid off. Length and on off. Stokes mistimes his loft but clears mid off to bag a boundary.
Length and outside off. Ben hits it on the off side.
Fuller and on off. Blocked out.
On the pads, nudged to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Improvisation! A flatter ball, on middle. Stokes reverse sweeps it to point for a boundary. 50-run stand is up between these two. It's so easy right now for the English batters.
SIX! This is huge! Tossed up, full and on off. Stokes advances down the track and tonks it well over long on for a biggie. 300 up for England.
Outside off. Defended out.
Darted on the pads, tucked to square leg for one.
Full and on off, pushed to covers for a single.
Shorter and outside off, cut away to deep point for a single. 13 coming off the over.
Slants a length ball, on off. Stokes blocks it on the surface.
Length and on middle. Stokes wrists it to deep square leg for a single.
On middle. Root defends with soft hands to mid-wicket and runs across for a quick single.
Touch fuller, angling outside off. Stokes again tries to go big but does not middle it, hits it in the air and over covers for a brace.
Full and on off, pushed to mid off.
Very full and on middle. This is hit to deep backward square leg for one.
Flatter and turning around middle. Stokes rocks back and plays it to mid-wicket.
Full and on off. Stokes reverse sweeps it to deep point for one more.
On middle, swept to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on off, pushed back to Permaul.

SIX! Fifty for Ben Stokes! What a way to reach a landmark! 27th half-century for Stokes! He took some time but looks well settled now. Flatter and outside off. Stokes comes down the track and hammers it straight down for a maximum.
Floated, full and on off. Stokes helps it to fine leg for a single.
Full ball, outside off. Stokes leans and punches it to deep cover for a single.
Lovely delivery! A length ball, outside off, nipping away a touch. Root looks to push but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and on middle, flicked to the right of mid-wicket.
Length and on off. Root is hurried as he defends this on the deck.
Very full and on middle. Root all day will flick this type of delivery to deep square leg. A single taken.
FOUR! Ends the over with a boundary! A full ball, on the pads. Stokes chips it aerially but no one is stationed at mid-wicket and the ball finds the fence.
Very full, on middle. Root pushes it to the left of mid-wicket where the fielder makes the stop.
Slower through the air, drifted onto middle. This one turns a bit and Joe Root stays watchful in defense.
On middle. Kept out.
Tossed up, on middle. Joe Root gets innovative now and attempts the reverse sweep. He can't get it past the point fielder though.
Floated up, full and on the pads. Root flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Ben Stokes shows all of his stumps and he makes room leg side. Permaul bowls it flatter and on off. Stokes looks to hammer it through extra cover but doesn't quite get the timing right.
FOUR! Alzarri Joseph looks for the toe-crushing yorker but spills it down leg. Joe Root just helps it on its way and picks up a boundary down to fine leg.
Angling on the pads, worked away leg side for a run.
Full and wide, its there to be hit. Ben Stokes makes room but can't get it past wide mid off. Single taken.
A length ball on off. Root blocks it out from his crease.
Back of a length, outside off. Joe Root hangs back and plays it awkwardly down towards backward point.
Excellent delivery! Good-length, close to the off pole. The ball straightens and zips past the outside edge of Root's blade as he has a half poke at it.
A touch quicker, spilled well down the leg side. Left alone.
Well, that was flashy! Ben Stokes switches to a right-hander and Permaul bowls it quicker around leg stump. Stokes misses the hard sweep and there's a bit of an extra bounce as well.

SIX! Muscled! Permaul holds the length back and bowls it on middle. Ben Stokes rocks back and pulls it all the way over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie. He was hitting against the wind there, but he doesn't care.
FOUR! Floated up, around off. Stokes hits it firmly off the back foot and goes over covers. He picks up another boundary.
Fuller and on off. Stokes reverse paddles it to deep backward point for a run.
This is pushed through on off. Root hangs back to defend.

FOUR! Poor bowling from Joseph. A length ball, width on offer and Stokes drives through the line and the ball races away to the cover fence. 100 partnership is up between these two and even more than 100 runs scored in the first session already.
FOUR! This is started to become a nightmare for the hosts now. Pitched up, on off. Ben Stokes goes up and over extra cover and picks up back-to-back boundaries. 350 up for England.

FOUR! Make that a hat-trick of boundaries now and Ben Stokes is eyeing a century before the Lunch break. This is pushed wider, Stokes moves outside off and drags it through mid-wicket for another boundary.

TWO LEG BYES! Two called straightaway and they race back for the second with ease in the end. On the pads, Stokes misses the flick and the ball goes off the pads behind square on the leg side. A couple of leg byes taken.
Stokes will feel he missed out on that one. Short and wide, Stokes hangs back and slaps it towards covers.

SIX! My word! This is something special we are witnessing here. Right in the slot outside off. Ben Stokes hangs back and smokes it a long, long way over the long on fence. This also brings up 5000 runs for him in Test cricket, becoming the 23rd English batter to do so.
Fullish delivery, floated up around off. Root bunts it out to cover-point for a single.
Holder comes from 'round the wicket and hurls across a slower length ball on middle. Stokes defends it back onto the deck.
Slower again, on off. Stokes presses forward and pushes it towards extra cover for a run.
Holder bowls another off cutter, around off. Root blocks it out on the off side.
Slower bouncer now on middle. Joe Root plays a lovely controlled pull shot and pulls it along the ground towards deep backward square leg for a couple.

Very full, on off. This is pushed down to long on for a single. Joe Root gets to his 150 and there is a huge roar from the crowd. Root raises his bat and it has been another classy innings from the English skipper.

Floated, very full and around leg stump. This is quicker at 91 clicks and Joe Root attempts the reverse sweep. He gets taken aback by the pace of the ball and the ball hits Root on the pads. A stifled appeal from the bowler.
Root premeditates with the reverse sweep and Brathwaite slows it up considerably. Root gets it down to third man and picks up a single.
Ouch! That is not advisable. Tossed up, on off. Stokes with a firm uppish drive, wide of the bowler and Kraigg Brathwaite just sticks out a left boot. The batters get a single.
On middle, driven towards mid on.
This is slowed up considerably again, just around 70 clicks. Root waits for it and works it towards square leg.
Brathwaite goes quicker, full and straight on the final ball. Joe Root digs it out and that will be Lunch on Day 2.
Holder starts off with a floater, on middle. Ben Stokes punches it down to long on for a single. Moves into the 90s now.
A length ball, slanting down the leg side. Root shuffles across and looks to flick it away but misses.
Pitched up, well outside off. Root watches it all the way through and makes the leave.
Holder bowls the cutter now, slow and on off. Joe Root works it towards square leg and turns the strike over. One-day tactics coming into play now and the field is well spread.
On off, eased down to long on for one more.
Open spaces on either side of the pitch and that's an easy single for Joe Root. Back of a length, on off. Root hops back and nudges it towards cover-point for a run.

OUT! LBW! Brilliant call from Jason Holder at first slip to press the issue and go for the review. This is a fullish delivery, around off and nipping back in quite a fair bit. Joe Root falls over a bit as he looks to push it out. The ball goes through the defense and raps him on the pads. The visitors appeal but they seem it's angling down leg. Holder pushes for the review and Brathwaite goes for it. No spike on UltraEdge and Ball Tracker comes up with three reds. Joe Root has to walk to huge applause after a wonderful knock and Kemar Roach moves up to 7th place in the leading wicket-takers for the Windies in Test cricket, surpassing Sir Garfield Sobers.
Howout: lbw b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Attacking the stumps and Bairstow defends it out.
A length ball, around off. Bairstow plays it towards point.
This is angled into middle, Jonny Bairstow is off the mark with a flick through mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Width on offer and Stokes taps it past point for a single. He will retain strike as well.
Pitched up, close to the off stump, from 'round the wicket. Stokes lets it through to the keeper.
Full and on off, driven towards wide mid off for a quick single.
On a nagging length and in that channel outside off. This is left alone.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Length this time, angled into off. Bairstow defends it out.
Full and outside off. Left alone by Bairstow.
Roach goes wide of off stump and Stokes shoulders arms.
A fuller ball, outside off. Stokes blocks it very late, off the bottom part of the blade.
Fuller and on middle. Stokes flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Length and outside off. Stokes offers no shot.
Fuller and on off. Stokes plays it to long on for a single.
Two leg byes! Fuller and angling on the pads. Bairstow misses his flick. It goes off the pads to fine leg for two leg byes. Good running.
Full and outside off. Stokes gently defends it on the off side.
Fullish and outside off. Stokes is right behind the line to keep it out.
Very full and on middle. Stokes makes room and smashes it on the up but just short of mid off.
Short of a length, slower and outside off. Stokes dabs it softly to deep point for a single.
Fuller and on off. This is hit to mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, driven to the left of mid off for a quick single.
Around middle and slanting into the pads. Bairstow flicks it awkwardly towards mid-wicket.
Misfield and they steal a single. Fuller and on the pads. Bairstow clips it straight to Jermaine Blackwood at mid-wicket who lets it through and allows the single.
Pitched up, around off. Stokes punches it firmly back towards the bowler.
Roach bowls it slower at just 103 clicks and on middle. Ben Stokes uses his wrists to turn it down to long on for a run.
Right on the money from Roach. Jonny Bairstow stays solid in defense.
Sliding down the leg side, helped down to fine leg for a run by Bairstow.
Full and on off, driven straight to mid off.
FOUR! Straight as an arrow! Overpitched on off, Jonny Bairstow with a lovely straight drive back past the bowler and the ball races away to the fence.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Jonny Bairstow. Half-volley, on off. Bairstow keeps his head still and exquisitely pushes it through covers for another boundary.
On off, pushed away towards cover.
This is spilled down the leg side, Bairstow misses the flick.
On a good length, around off. Bairstow hangs back and keeps it out on the off side.
Back of a length, close to the off pole. Stokes hops and nudges it down to deep backward point for one.
Nicely bowled! Slanted into middle and leg. Bairstow looks to turn it leg side but gets a leading edge towards covers.
Fuller, around off and nipping in. Bairstow manages to keep it out.
This time, on the pads. Defended to short mid-wicket.
Full and straight, punched towards mid on.
Pitched up on middle and leg. Bairstow defends it towards short mid-wicket yet again.
Pitched up from 'round the wicket and around the fifth stump line, Stokes shoulders arms to it.
On off, defended off the front foot towards cover.
Use of the feet from Ben Stokes and maybe some jitters out there as he's on 99. A length ball, slanting in from off and Stokes taps it towards covers.

A century to savour for Ben Stokes! The crowd is up on its feet and Stokes looks up to the heavens and up to his late father. Length, around off, bunted out on the off side. Jonny Bairstow is alive to the situation and responds quickly. They scamper through and Stokes has his first hundred in the Caribbean.
Good-length, on off. Tapped towards covers.
On off again, Bairstow stays solid in defense.
Back of a length, around off. Stokes hangs back and taps it towards covers.
On middle, pushed down to long on for a single.
Pitched up, angling into off. Bairstow presses forward to defend.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Jonny Bairstow. Short and wide, it's the back of the hand slower ball. Bairstow picks it up and slaps it through cover-point for a boundary. England go past the 400-run mark.
On middle, Bairstow defends it off the front foot.
A length ball, on off. Bairstow keeps it out.
Length and down the leg side. Stokes misses his flick.
Length again, slanting on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
On the pads this time, Stokes bunts it to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller ball, on middle. Bairstow pushes it softly to mid on.
Short ball, drifting on middle. Bairstow keeps his bat close to his body and watches it bounce over.
Overpitched, on middle, flicked to deep mid-wicket for an easy couple.
Very full and outside off. Stokes works it to long off for a single.
Another single as this is pushed to point.
Length ball, way outside off. Stokes slaps it to long off for a single.
A length ball, around off. Bairstow defends it to point.
Might be the back of the hand delivery, around off, pulled to deep square leg for a single.
West Indies have gone full defensive as mostly all the players are standing in the deep. This is full and on middle. Stokes hits it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short in length, around off, extra bounce there. Stokes looks to ramp it away but gets beaten by the bounce.
Around off, pushed to covers for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! Jonny Bairstow is livid with himself! Alzarri Joseph goes wide of the crease and angles a length ball, outside off. Bairstow thinks to hook it away but it goes off the leading edge, in the air and to deep mid-wicket where Nkrumah Bonner takes it. West Indies get the centurion in Antigua for a timid score this time.
Howout: c Nkrumah Bonner b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Length ball, angling on middle. Blocked out.
Well outside off and Foakes is happy to leave it.
Length ball, closer this time but wide enough for Foakes to leave it alone.
Fuller and outside off. Stokes smacks it wide of deep cover for a couple of runs.
SIX! BANG! Slower through the air, flatter and around off. Stokes swings across and this goes right from the middle and over mid-wicket for a biggie.

SIX! Just, just over John Campbell! Shorter this time, on off. Stokes pulls it to wide of long on. John Campbell there tracks back and takes the catch but he stepped over the ropes and it goes for a maximum.

OUT! TAKEN! Kraigg Brathwaite gets the big wicket. Ben Stokes tries to go big again but holes one out. A short ball again was way outside off. Stokes stands tall and tries to hit it over covers but it goes off the toe end of his bat, to deep cover where Shamarh Brooks takes it with ease. Ben Stokes gets a standing ovation for his wonderful knock.
Howout: c Shamarh Brooks b Kraigg Brathwaite

Commentary: Flighted, flatter and around off. Woakes on the back foot, works it to short mid-wicket.
On the pads, Woakes keeps it out. 14 runs and a big wicket of Stokes from the over.
Fuller and outside off, pushed to covers.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Length again, Foakes punches off the back foot to point.
Length ball, outside off. Foakes offers no shot.
FOUR! Foakes is off the mark with a boundary. Length ball, outside off. Foakes steers it through point for a boundary.
Length and outside off. Foakes lets it through.
Full and angling on the pads. Woakes gets low and sweeps it to square leg for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off. Foakes leans and blocks it to covers.
Full and on middle, worked to mid-wicket.
Slower ball, flighted and on middle, Foakes skips down and wrists it to mid-wicket.
A single as this full ball is flicked to deep square leg.
Floated, full and on middle. Woakes tucks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, nipping back in around off. Foakes steps across and blocks it.
Length and outside off. Foakes punches it to deep point for a single.
Almost chopped on! Short of a length, outside off. Woakes looks to pull but gets an inside edge, past the off stump and to fine leg. A single taken.
On middle, Woakes hits it to mid-wicket for a single.
Another single as this length ball is pushed to long on.
Length ball, outside off. Woakes on his toes taps it to covers for one more.
Darted on the pads, Woakes turns it to mid-wicket for one more.
Full and on middle. Foakes eases it to long on for a couple of runs.
Flighted ball, on off, pushed to mid off.
Floated, on the pads, flicked to mid-wicket.
Darted on the pads. Ben tickles it to fine leg for a single.
An arm ball, on middle. Woakes strides forward and blocks it.
Full and on off, pushed to covers.
An arm ball, angling around off. Foakes defends on time.
A low dipping full toss, on middle, drilled to long on for one.
A single as this is pushed to long on.
A loopy ball, on off, Foakes works it to covers for a single.
Very full this time and Woakes jams it back to the bowler.
This is floated outside off. Foakes walks towards the ball and pushes it to the left of mid off for a single.
On the pads, worked to deep square leg by Woakes for one more.
Slowed up, on middle. Foakes reaches out and pushes back to the bowler.
Drifted onto the pads, Ben Foakes tickles it behind square on the leg side for another single.
Flighted delivery, around leg stump. Woakes knocks it 'round the corner and turns the strike over.
Brathwaite keeps it around leg and this is turned through square leg for a fifth single in the over.
Lovely! Flighted, drift in towards off stump. The ball drips and turns after pitching. Foakes looks to blocks but gets beaten past the outside edge.
On middle, driven through mid on for a single.
Slower through the air, flighted on middle. Woakes with a gentle push down the ground for a run. The 450 is up now for England.
Around off, pushed towards covers.
Looped up on middle. Foakes pushes it through mid off and collects a single.
On the pads, nudged away on the leg side.
Pushed through on middle. Foakes clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
Considerably slowed up this time. Woakes blocks it out.
Brathwaite darts this one in at 95 ckph. Woakes makes the block.
On leg stump, flicked away towards short fine leg for an easy single.
A bit of a fumble from Kraigg Brathwaite but he recovers well. On middle, firmly pushed towards the bowler who gets a hand on it but is quick to chase it down and stop the single.
This one almost never artives. At just 61 kph and on leg. Ben Foakes reaches out and brooms it to deep backward square leg for a run.
