Flatter, on off. Kept out on the off side.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Drifted into middle and leg, worked to wide long on for one more.
And again! Tossed up, on middle. Woakes pushes it through mid on for a single.

Flatter this time and on off. Foakes reaches out to defend. It's all a bit slow out there at the moment. Something has to give and soon or else the visitors will keep on piling the runs, slowly but surely.
Around off, pushed towards covers.
Shorter in length, angled across off. Woakes rocks back and pushes it to long off for a single.
Around off, pushed towards mid off.
At just 69 kph, Ben Foakes comes down the track and drives it down to long on for a single.
This is spilled down the leg side, Woakes sweeps it down to fine leg for a run.
Around middle and leg, Foakes uses his feet again but this time there's a silly mid on in place.
Outside off, driven towards covers for a single.
Angles a full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle. Foakes prods and blocks it.
This one lands on off and spins away. Foakes lunges and defends it out.
Full and on off, pushed to long off for a single.
On off. Blocked out.
Flatter and on off. Woakes defends it to covers.
Full and on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Floated, full and on middle. Woakes on his front foot to block it.
Another solid block from Woakes.
Flatter, quicker and on off. Woakes pushes back to the bowler.
Down the leg side, Woakes sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
Shorter and angling across. Foakes defends with soft hands to first slip.
Tossed up, on off. Defended out.
SIX! HUGE! Tossed up, full and outside off. Woakes slog-sweeps it over mid-wicket for a biggie.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up,full and on off, it lands and spins away. Woakes looks to sweep it but misses and gets hit on the pads. A half-hearted appeal for LBW follows.
Floated, on off, pushed back to Permaul.
Full and on off. Woakes drills it to long on for a single.
Flatter and on off, very slow in the air. Blocked out.
Slow again, short and on off. Woakes cuts it to mid-wicket where the fielder makes a good stop.
FOUR! This was short and outside off, Woakes looks to cut but it goes of the outside edge to the third man fence. A 50-run stand between these two comes up...
On middle. Defended out.
Quicker this time, on middle. Woakes turns it to long on for a single. Kraigg Brathwaite steps over and a no ball is given.
Full and on off. Foakes comes down and drills it to long off for one more.
Full and on leg, swept to deep square leg for a single.
Full, outside off, width given and this is driven to deep point for a single.
Short and on off. Foakes makes room and losses his stance but still hits it to deep cover for a single.
Another single as this is worked to deep cover.
Full and on off, pushed to long off for a single.
An appeal for caught behind but not given! Floated, full and outside off. Woakes prods to defend but the ball turns shade away and gets beaten on the outside edge. The replay confirms no bat there.
Floated again, angling on off. Woakes looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball lobs well wide of first slip. That will be Tea on Day 2.
Runs straightaway. Pitched up on off, Foakes pushes it out towards covers for a single.
Good short ball from Kemar Roach, a bit of an intent shown. On middle, at helmet height and Woakes just about manages to duck under it.
A length ball, around off. This is dabbed down towards backward point.

FOUR! First boundary of the session and it comes off Woakes' bat. On a driving length, a bit wide of off stump. Woakes goes chasing after it and gets an outside edge that runs away into the third man fence.
A slower bumper now, outside off and the ball dies on its way to Joshua Da Silva.
Appeal from the bowler but the keeper doesn't seem interested. Banged in short and down the leg side. Woakes looks to pull but misses.
Flatter and around off. Firmly pushed towards covers.
On a length, around off and there's a bit of turn as well. Ben Foakes works it to sweeper cover for a single.
Shorter and around off. Woakes goes on the back foot and punches it towards covers.

FOUR BYES! Well, that's unlucky for the bowler. Nicely flighted and drifted into middle. Chris Woakes looks to step out but gets beaten in flight completely. The ball goes through bat and pad, eludes the keeper and races away into the fence.
Quicker and flatter, around off. This is cut away through point for one.
On the pads, nudged away onto the leg side for a quick single.
Great stop from John Campbell. A length ball, on off. Foakes flicks it to the right of mid-wicket but can't get it past the fielder.
Quick single and they get through easily in the end. On middle, pushed towards mid on for a single.
Short ball, around off. This is pulled away through mid-wicket by Woakes for another single.
Length this time, close to the off pole. Foakes defends it out.

Sliding into middle and leg, clipped away to deep square leg for a single. There hasn't been a single maiden over since the 73rd over of the innings and England inching ever closer to the 500-run mark.
On middle, flicked away to mid-wicket.
Nicely bowled! Drifted into middle, Foakes defends it out.
Around off, cut away off the back foot to deep point for one.
On off, Chris Woakes uses his feet to drive it down towards wide long on for a single.

OUT! STUMPED! Classic off-spinner's dismissal and Veerasammy Permaul has his man. Nicely flighted, outside off and on a driving length. Ben Foakes is enticed into playing the drive but the ball is slower and there's turn on offer too. Foakes gets beaten in flight and Joshua Da Silva has way too much time to whips off the bails. Foakes departs with a score of 499 and finally there's some respite for Permaul.
Howout: st Joshua Da Silva b Veerasammy Permaul

Commentary: Darted into middle. Blocked out.
On middle again, nudged onto the leg side.
Roach is pepping Woakes with good short balls. This is over leg stump and Woakes is just not ready for it. Luckily for him, there's no edge on that one.
FOUR! Hoicked away and the 500 is up for England! Slower one, on the pads. Woakes gets down on one knee and whips it to the left of fine leg for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! The short ball ploy has worked for Kemar Roach and the Windies and the last recognized batter is back in the hut. Roach steams in and digs in another short ball, around the batter's helmet. Chris Woakes looks to take it on as he makes a bit of room and attempts the swat. The ball goes off the toe end of the bat and towards mid-wicket. A couple of fielders converge but its Jayden Seales who runs in from deep mid-wicket and takes a fine sliding catch.
Howout: c Jayden Seales b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Angled into the pads, Fisher misses the tuck and the ball goes off the pads towards the keeper.
Short again, over middle. Matthew Fisher ducks under it.
Another spicy short ball, over middle again. Fisher does well to get his head under it in time.
Flatter and spinning around middle. Leach looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Around off, fuller and this is blocked out.
FOUR! Tossed up, outside off. Leack steps down and smashes it through covers for a boundary.
Tossed up, on off. Defended out.

OUT! STUMPING! Joe Root calls their batters and that will be the end of England's innings. Tossed up, full and outside off, turn again. Leach comes down the track and looks to heave but misses and the ball sneaks through. Joshua Da Silva behind removes the bails easily. England declare their innings at 507/9.
Howout: st Joshua Da Silva b Veerasammy Permaul

Commentary: A length ball, on off, hint of away shape. Brathwaite defends it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! West Indies and Brathwaite are off the mark! A length ball, outside off, width there as well. Brathwaite punches off the back foot through point for a boundary.
Length ball, outside off. Brathwaite shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! Good start for the Windies! Fuller and on off. Brathwaite this time, leans and punches down to long off for another boundary.
Length and on the pads, flicked wide of deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Fuller and outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Just like Brathwaite, Campbell is off the mark with a boundary! Fullish and around off. Campbell leans and pushes it through point for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A dream start for the debutant and he is running all over with joy in his eyes! A length ball, in good channel, around 4th stump channel. John Campbell has a poke at it but gets a thin outside edge to the keeper and Ben Foakes is not making any mistake. What a start to Fisher's Test career!
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Matthew Fisher

Commentary: Extra pace, bounce, outside off. Brooks offers no shot.
Length ball, around off. Brooks has his line covered as he defends this.
Length ball, outside off, it hits the deck and jags in sharply. Brooks shoulders arms to it.
On a length, around middle, extra bounce. Defended on the deck.
Length ball, a slight shape of outward movement, on middle. Brathwaite blocks it to mid-wicket.
Touch fuller, on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller again, outside off. Brathwaite watchfully leaves it.
Length ball, shaping away after landing outside off. Brathwaite shoulders arms to it.
Drags his length back, on off. Brathwaite hops and blocks it.
Good shape again! Length ball, outside off, moving away. Brathwaite leaves it. Also, that is the first maiden over of the whole Day.
Full and on off. Brooks defends it to mid on.
Length ball, hits the deck hard. Brooks defends off the splice of the bat.
Four byes! A pacy short ball, on middle, the ball hows late movement and goes to the left of the keeper. Hard for him to catch it and the ball finds the fence.
Full and on middle. Brooks flicks it through mid-wicket. Saqib Mahmood gives a chase and saves a run.
Length ball, on off. Kept out.
Length again. Brathwaite dead bats it on the off side.
A length ball, outswinger this time and Brooks covers his stumps nicely.
Outside off, on a length. Brooks shoulders arms to it.
Brooks with yet another easy leave.
Length ball, shaping away, outside off and steep bounce as well. All for Brooks to shoulders his arms.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball, on the pads, tucked to square leg.
Short and wide, Kraigg Brathwaite rocks back to cut but doesn't time it well enough. Just a single then towards point.
Down the leg side, tucked away off the hips to fine leg for one more.
Full and close to the off pole. Brathwaite defends it out solidly.
Excellent running! On off, Brathwaite drops it towards short cover and sees the fielder is a bit further back. Calls for the single and scampers through quickly.
A length ball on middle. Brooks blocks it out towards mid on.
Full, on the sixth stump and at 137 clicks. Brooks isn't going to play at that one.
Well bowled! A touch fuller, angled into middle and nipping away off the pitch. Brathwaite has a shuffle across but gets caught on the creases and edges it towards the slip cordon.
A length ball, on off. Brathwaite pushes it out towards covers.
Woakes hits the length hard and bowls it around off. Brathwaite hops back and keeps it down on the deck but is a bit taken aback by the extra bit of bounce.
On a good length around off. Blocked.
Pitched up, a bit outside off and shaping away. Brathwaite shoulders arms.
Maiden! Full and straight, Brathwaite times the straight drive well but the fielder at mid on does well to make a sharp stop down to his left.
Leach starts off with a flatter one, pushed through around off. Brooks can't get it past point.
FOUR! Short and wide, Shamarh Brooks rocks back and slaps it through cover-point for a boundary.
Half an appeal, nothing more. On a length, around middle. Brooks gets a big stride forward and looks to sweep but misses. He misses and gets hit on the pads but the umpire remains unmoved.
Peach! Tossed up, full and around off. The ball grips and turns away sharply. Brooks does well not to edge that one.
Tossed up again, wide of off. Kept out on the off side.
Around off and turning away, left alone.
Angled onto the pads, tucked away behind square on the leg side for a single by Brathwaite.
Brilliant delivery and a leave to match. Fullish delivery, angled into off and getting it to deviate away off the pitch. Brooks makes a watchful leave.
This is dragged down around off. Brooks hangs back and dabs it through covers for a single.
Good-length on off, Brathwaite plays it off the back foot onto the off side and collects a single.
Edged and four! On a driving length, outside off. Shamarh Brooks pushes away from the body and edges it down to the vacant third man fence for a boundary.
Around the top of off, kept out on the off side.
Flatter, on off and at 90 kph. Brathwaite presses forward to make the block.
Quicker and shorter, around off. Brathwaite goes deep in his crease to keep it out towards covers.
Around off, defended towards short cover this time.
Full and around the leg stump, Brathwaite nudges it behind towards short fine leg.
Around middle and leg, played with soft hands towards short leg by Brathwaite.
This is pushed through on off. Brathwaite goes on the back foot to keep it out.
Full and on middle. Brooks leans and solidly blocks it.
Length ball, hint of outswing, on off. Brooks gets a straight bat down to defend.
A stifled appeal for LBW but not given! A length ball, on off. Brooks looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Length again, on off. Brooks defends with an angled bat.
Fuller and outside off. Brooks times his drive but Stokes does well at covers to stop it.
FOUR! A length ball, outside off, shaping away. Brooks looks to punch off the back foot but gets an outside edge, just past gully for a boundary.
Tossed up, on middle. Brathwaite strides forward to defend it.
Two byes! Flatter and down the leg side. Brathwaite misses his flick. The keeper fails to collect and the batters take two byes.
On middle. Blocked out.
Full and on off. Brathwaite defends on the front foot.
Tossed up, on off. Brathwaite with another solid block.
Leach comes over the wicket this time, flatter and on off. Brathwaite blocks it off the back foot.
Length and on off. Brooks keeps it out.
Length and outside off. Brooks plays it late and without much commitment, to the keeper.
Down the leg side. Brooks misses his flick.
Short and well outside off. Brooks watches it sail over and to the keeper.

NOT OUT! A foot forward and that might have been a good catch. Fisher goes wide of the crease and angles a full ball, around off. Brooks closes his bat face slightly as he tries to defend on the leg side but gets an outside edge to second slip where Crawley gets his hands low to take it but he seems to have not taken it cleanly. The catch is taken upstairs and the replay shows the ball was grounded.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off. Brooks gets low and caresses it through covers for a boundary.
Very full and on off, pushed to covers.
Tossed up, full and on off. Brathwaite dead bats it.
Quicker one, on off. Brathwaite again blocks it.
Shorter, outside off, spinning away. Left alone.
Quicker again, on middle. Brathwaite prods and defends it solidly.
On middle. Defended out.
Short of a length, on off. Brooks gets on his toes to defend it.
Length and on middle, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Length and angling on off. Brathwaite covers his stumps and blocks it.
Length and outside off. Brathwaite defends away from the body, onto the off side.
Full, outside off, left alone.
Pitches it up, on middle. Brathwaite leans and defends it off the outer portion.
This is pushed through fuller and around off. Brooks blocks it out.
Quicker and flatter, on off. Brooks works it off the back foot towards short cover.
Flatter again, darted into middle. There's an extra bit of bounce as Brooks looks to defend but manages to keep it down on the off side.
FOUR! Just straying a bit there Jack Leach and Shamarh Brooks takes full advantage. Down the leg side, paddled away into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Shorter again, pushed towards covers by Brooks for a quick single.
On off. Brathwaite defends it under the eyeline.
Stokes bangs it in short and over middle. Brooks ducks under it.
Back of a length, around off. Brooks hops back and keeps it down towards cover.
Length this time, around off and at 139 kph. Brooks defends it back onto the deck.
Nicely bowled shorter ball. This is angled into off but goes straight through. Shamarh Brooks does well to sway away from the line of the ball.
NO BALL! Pitched up, on off. Brooks defends it off the front foot. Stokes has overstepped and a no ball is called.
This is slanted down the leg side. Brooks misses the tuck.
Full and wide, left alone by Shamarh Brooks.
Mahmood starts off with a full ball, on the fifth stump line. Brathwaite watches it zip through to the keeper.
Around the top of off, at 137 clicks. Brathwaite keeps it out on the off side.
Nicely bowled! A touch fuller, into that channel around off and just shaping away a bit. Brathwaite looks to have a poke at it but decides against it in the end.
Back of a length, around off. Brathwaite dabs it down towards cover-point.
On a good length over off. Saqib Mahmood is keeping it around the 135 kph mark. Kraigg Brathwaite with another defensive block off the back foot.
Starts off with a maiden does Saqib Mahmood. Length, sliding onto the pads. Brathwaite fails to get it away.
Back of a length, around off. This is caressed towards cover-point.
Full, close to the off pole and left alone by Brooks.
Fullish delivery around off. Shamarh Brooks doesn't quite time the cover drive but still picks up a single.
Pitched up, around off. Brathwaite shoulders arms to it.
Slanted into middle and leg, kept out on the leg side. The English crowd is getting louder and louder every second, pushing their team to pick up a wicket.
On a good length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it towards the cover region.
Short ball, on off. Brooks is not tempted to pull this one.
Length and outside off. Brooks shoulders arms to it.
Length ball, outside off. Brooks hops and blocks it out. A late no ball called for overstepping.
Length ball, angling around off. Brooks defends with a straight bat.
Length again, on middle. Brooks wrists it but straight to mid-wicket.
Bangs a bouncer now, on middle. Brooks sits under it.
Extra bounce this time, outside off. Brooks easily leaves it.
Tossed up, full and on off. Brathwaite prods and defends.
Floated, full, outside off. Brathwaite prods and shoulders arms to it.
Spin there again, around off. Brathwaite defends on the front foot.

NOT OUT! A flatter ball, angling around middle. Brathwaite looks to defend but the ball does not bounce much and he gets hit on the pads. An appeal and up goes the finger. Brathwaite though reviews it straightaway and he looked confident as well. The replay shows there was a big spike as the ball passes the bat. Good review.
Very full, slanting on middle. Brathwaite whips it to mid-wicket for a brace.
Darted on the pads. Brathwaite nudges it to square leg.
Length and on middle. Brooks tucks it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, outside off. Brooks punches it hard and to point where Lees certainly saves a boundary,
This time hits it through covers for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Brathwaite tries to nudge it down but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls to covers and they take a quick single.
Full ball, inswinger, on middle. Brooks on drives it to mid on.
Length ball, outside off. Brooks leaves it alone.
Floated, full and on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it past mid-wicket and picks up a couple of runs.
Nicely drifted into middle. Brathwaite strides forward to make the block.
Nicely bowled! Drifted into middle and leg, at a nagging length and turning away nicely. Kraigg Brathwaite with another good forward defensive shot.
FOUR! Drift on offer but Jack Leach errs in line this time as he bowls it quicker. Kraigg Brathwaite rocks back and cuts it into the point fence. The 50 partnership is up between theses two.
Good comeback delivery fro Leach. Slower through the air, turning away quite a bit from middle. Brathwaite edges it down with soft hands towards the slip cordon.
Around off. Blocked.
Full, on the sixth stump line at 138 clicks. Brooks shoulders arms to that one.
Top delivery and a very good leave in the end by Shamarh Brooks. Length, very close to the off pole and holding its line. Brooks looks to have a poke at it but decides against it.
On off. Blocked off.
This pitched up, a bit wide of off stump. Brooks isn't going to play at that one.
Good-length, around the top of off. Brooks goes back and across to push it out on the off side.
Fuller in length, gently driven towards mid off. Maiden!
Angled into middle and leg, a touch quicker though. Brathwaite keeps it out.
Slightly tossed up, full and staright. Brathwaite drives it towards mid on.
This is pushed through on off. The ball turns away a bit and Brathwaite plays it well.
Around off, kept down past the slip cordon.
And again! Leach is just bowling it at the same pace and around off. Brathwaite with another easy block.
FOUR! A bit of width on offer and Kraigg Brathwaite is waiting for it. Brathwaite rocks back and strokes it through backward point for a welcome boundary.
Around off, pushed towards the cover region for an easy single.
On a length, around off. The ball turns in and Lawrence gets a bit of bounce as well. Brathwaite dabs it down on the leg side.
Around middle, gently pushed towards mid on.
Nicely bowled! Flighted, on off and Lawrence puts a bit of revs on that one. Brathwaite nudges it towards square leg for one.
This is fired in full and outside off. Brooks doesn't play at it.
Dragged down now, on leg stump. Brooks pulls it down to fine leg for a single.
Jaffa! Nicely drifted into middle, on a length and the ball just takes off after pitching. The ball is bowled at 80 kph, it turns away sharply and bounces extra. Shamarh Brooks is left bamboozled.
A touch quicker, on middle and turning away. Brooks keeps it out this time.
On off, dabbed down towards silly point.
This is pushed through on off and Shamarh Brooks defends it right off the middle of the bat past silly point.
Turning sharply from a nagging length. Brooks goes deep in his crease and plays at it with soft hands towards the gully region.
Well negated by Shamarh Brooks and he has seen it through. This is flatter and on off. Brooks defends it off the back foot towards short cover and that will be curtains on Day 2!
Fisher is on the money right from the off. A length ball, on off. Brathwaite blocks it out.
A touch fuller this time, around off. Brathwaite presses forward to defend.
On a good length, over middle. Brathwaite looks to defend but gets taken aback by the extra bounce but manages to keep it down.
Around the top of off, kept out.
Pitched up on off. This one stays a tad low but Brathwaite stays solid in defense.
Fisher starts Day 3 with a maiden! On a good length, angled into middle. There's a bit of an extra bounce again as Brathwaite dabs it down on the leg side.
What a delivery to start off with! Slowed up, at 77 kph and drifted into off. The ball grips and turns away sharply leaving Brooks completely bamboozled.
On middle. Kept out.
This is sliding into middle and leg. Brooks flicks it through mid-wicket and picks up the first run of the day.
Peach! Lovely drift and then sharp turn again from Jack Leach. Brathwaite presses forward to block but gets beaten past the outside edge.
Around middle, Brathwaite looks to push it out but gets it just to the right of short leg and scampers through for a single.
Floated up on off. Brooks defends it out.
A length ball, on off and just nipping back in a touch. Brathwaite defends it from his crease.
Length again, around off. This is pushed away on the up towards covers.
Fullish ball, around middle and just swinging in a bit. Brathwaite bunts it out on the leg side.
Full again, on off and slanting in. Brathwaite manages to keep it out.
Sliding onto the pads, tucked away to deep square leg for one.
This is banged in halfway down, over off. Brooks ducks under it but the ball loops over his head and dies on its way to the keeper.
Quicker one, darted into middle at 92 kph. Brathwaite defend sit out.
Around off, Brathwaite gets a big stride forward and strokes it towards covers for a run.
Just a tad bit short now, on off. Brooks goes on the back foot to block it out.
Flatter, on off. Blocked.
Shorter and wider, punched off the back foot through covers. Ben Stokes gives chase and slides in to cut off the boundary. The batters should have got three but they settle for a brace.
Flatter and on off. Defended out by Brooks.
Back of a length, cutting into off. Brathwaite hops back to defend.
This is banged in a bit and at the pads. The ball doesn't bounce much this time and Brathwaite tucks it towards Jonny Bairstow at leg gully.
Good-length, around off. This is tapped towards covers.
Around the top of off. Brathwaite pushes it out with soft hands towards mid off.
Length again, on off. Blocked out.
On a good length, on the fifth stump line. Brathwaite keeps it out on the off side and it will be another maiden here for Matthew Fisher.
On off. Defended out.
This is flighted on the pads. Shamarh Brooks flicks it behind square on the leg side for a couple. And again, it should have been three runs.
On middle, Brooks solidly keeps it out.
Another well bowled delivery from Leach. Drifting onto middle and turning away. Shamarh Brooks does well to play at it with soft hands as he edges it down past the slip cordon for a single.
On middle, kept out.
This is pushed through on middle. Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Pitched up on off. Brooks presents a dead bat at it.

Just short! On a good length, sliding in from outside off. There's a bit of an extra bounce on offer and Shamarh Brooks gets caught off guard. The ball goes off the gloves but falls just in front of a diving Zak Crawley at second slip.
On off, this is kept out on the off side.
Full and wide, left alone.
A short ball, this is banged in wide of the off stump. Brooks isn't going to play at that one.
A length ball, slanting down leg. This is tucked away 'round the corner for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Brooks comes forward a bit and pushes it past the diving bowler for a single.
Flighted around leg. Kraigg Brathwaite steps out and works it towards wide mid on for a single that too against the turn.
Pushed through on off and turning away. Defended off the back foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! England do have the early breakthrough and it's Jack Leach who has provided it. Leach mixes up his length and bowls it a tad shorter this time and around off. The ball turns away but it is there to cut. Shamarh Brooks rocks back but is a bit too early into his cut. Brooks ends up playing a false shot and slices it towards point. Chris Woakes over there takes a good low catch and the Windies will have to start from scratch yet again.
Howout: c Chris Woakes b Jack Leach

Commentary: Full, around middle and leg. This is eased to mid on.
Quicker and fuller, at the stumps. Bonner keeps it out.
Back of a length, on the hips. This is worked through the mid-wicket region for a single.
Pitched up, outside off. Nkrumah Bonner makes an easy leave.
A length ball, on the sixth stump line and there's just a bit of movement in the air for Mahmood. Bonner makes a watchful leave.
Nicely bowled! Length again, angled in from outside off but the ball holds its line. Bonner looks to block from the crease but gets beaten past the outside edge.
Shortish length, on middle. Bonner defends it back onto the deck.
This one shapes in from outside off. Bonner dead bats it onto the off side.
Pushed through on off. Kept out.
Quicker and flatter, on off. Brathwaite defends it out.
This is speared in full and on middle. Brathwaite does well to get a bat on it.
Around off, Brathwaite strides out to defend.
On off this time, defended towards silly point.
On a length, sliding into middle and leg. Brathwaite wrists it towards square leg. Maiden over from Jack Leach.
A length ball, close to the off pole. Bonner defends it out with soft hands towards covers.
Pitched up, around off and there's late inward movement after the ball passes the batter. Bonner makes a watchful leave.
This is wide of the off stump. Bonner isn't interested in playing at that one.
Full and straight, gently driven back towards the bowler.
Shorter in length, around the hips. Nkrumah Bonner drags the pull shot down to fine leg and picks up a single.
On off. Defended towards silly mid on.
Flatter, around off. Bonner opens the face of the bat and plays it towards backward point.
Sliding into middle and leg, Bonner looks to drive but gets it off the inside edge and through his pads.
Jaffa! Drifted onto leg stump, the ball hits a crack and just turns square. Nkrumah Bonner is left bamboozled.
On off, kept out.
Quicker, drifted onto the pads and turning away. Bonner strides out to defend.
Flatter this time, this is played off the back foot towards covers. Another maiden for Jack Leach.
Pitched up, on off and just shaping away a bit. Brathwaite gets a leading edge down towards cover-point.
Trying to attack the pads on the full but spills it down the leg side does Woakes. Brathwaite misses the flick.
Uppish but safe! Full and wide, Kraigg Brathwaite reaches for this one and drives it on the bounce to the man at point.
This is a bit fuller and nipping back into middle. Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
On off. Blocked out.
This is slanted into middle, the ball bounces a bit extra and hits the high part of Brathwaite's willow.
Tossed up at 92 kph and on middle. Bonner drives it to the left of the bowler.
FOUR! Nkrumah Bonner is the man in form and after blocking everything, he gets one away. Spilled down the leg side and this is swept away to the backward square leg fence for a boundary.
Leach drags back his length and bowls it on off. Bonner defends it off the back foot.
Pushed through close to the off stump and turning away slightly. Bonner makes an assured leave.
FOUR! Slightly overpitched from Leach and Nkrumah Bonner drives it through extra cover for another boundary.
On middle. Blocked out.
This is fuller and on the pads, Brathwaite flicks it in front of square on the leg side and picks up a couple of runs.
A length ball, around the top of middle. Brathwaite keeps it out towards mid on.
FOUR! Nicely timed! The hosts moving along nicely here. On the pads, worked away through square leg and Kraigg Brathwaite picks up a boundary.
On middle and leg, nudged away to mid-wicket for a single. The 100 is up for the hosts.
Right around the top of off and good seam position. Bonner blocks it out watchfully.
A tighter line, close to the off pole. Nkrumah Bonner makes an assured leave.
Stokes starts off with a gentle-paced delivery, sliding into middle and leg. This one keeps low and Brathwaite does well to keep it out.
Leg bye! Drifted onto the pads, Brathwaite looks to tuck it away but the ball comes off the pads and goes past the keeper. Foakes chases it down and keeps it down to a single.
Around middle and leg, turned to the fielder at square leg.
Length ball, on off. Nkrumah Bonner looks to drive on the up but gets an inside edge back onto the pads.
Length again, well outside off. Bonner lets it through to the keeper.
On off, punched away towards cover.
On a good length, over middle. Brathwaite turns it past the fielder at short mid-wicket but doesn't go for the single.
Around the hips, tucked away leg side.
A bit of width on offer. Brathwaite plays away from the body and taps it straight to point.
Woakes hits the length hard and bowls it on off. Brathwaite hangs back to defend it out.
Length again, on off. Defended off the front foot.
Angled into the off stump. Brathwaite stays solid in defense.
Full, on the sixth stump line and shaping away nicely. Bonner leaves it alone.
Full again, a bit closer to the off stump this time and Bonner makes another easy leave.

OUT! LBW! The centurion from the previous match is gone! Ben Stokes is having a dream of a Test match and he gets the big breakthrough. A length ball, this is slanted in from well outside off. Nkrumah Bonner is pushed onto the back foot as he looks to flick it away. Bonner gets caught on the crease and gets trapped in front. He reviews it straightaway. The third umpire checks UltraEdge thoroughly as there is a spike but it is off the pads and the ball just missed the bat, he concludes. Ball Tracker shows that the impact is in line and the ball is just hitting the top of off. England in the driving seat now and Bonner has to walk back.
Howout: lbw b Ben Stokes

Commentary: A length ball, angling in from outside off and just holds its line. Left alone by Blackwood.
Fullish delivery, outside off. Blackwood doesn't play at it.
On middle this time, Blackwood defend sit out. A wicket-maiden for Ben Stokes.
On middle, driven off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
Around the top of off. Pushed out onto the off side off the back foot.
Back of a length, around the hips. Brathwaite does well to keep it down on the leg side.
length this time, close to the off pole. Brathwaite taps it towards the cover region.
Woakes hits the length hard and bowls it around off. Brathwaite taps it back onto the deck.
And again! On off, Brathwaite stays solid in defense. Another maiden over for England.
Around the top of off, Blackwood hangs back and eases it on the off side.
Fuller this time, around off. This is stroked away towards covers.
On off, Blackwood defends it with a straight bat.
This is sliding onto the pads. Tucked away leg side.

Huge appeal but in the end, Ben Stokes lets it go. Fullish ball, around off and nips back in sharply. Jermaine Blackwood gets stranded on the crease and gets rapped on the back leg. Stokes appeals but the umpire remains unmoved. He walks back to his mark. England have let one slip as the Ball Tracker shows that the wickets were hitting. Had they reviewed it, Blackwood would have been a goner.
On off, kept out.
Nicely tossed up on middle. Brathwaite keeps it out.
On middle. Blocked out.
Sliding into middle and leg. Brathwaite strides forward to defend.
This is a bit quicker and fuller, on middle. Brathwaite pushes it firmly towards mid on.
A touch slower through the air, on off. Brathwaite keeps it down towards silly point.
The maidens just keep on coming. Floated up, on off. Brathwaite presses forward to defend.
Fullish ball, outside off and shaping away. Blackwood mistimes the off drive off the back foot.
A length ball, over middle. Blackwood taps it back onto the deck.
Still no run. Full and wide, driven to the left of the fielder at cover who makes a good diving stop.
Length again, slanted into the pads. Blackwood misses the tuck and gets hit high on the pads.
Fullish delivery, around off and skidding through. Jermaine Blackwood defends it with authority.
FOUR! First runs off the bat after a while now and Jermaine Blackwood is off the mark as well. Full and wide, this is slashed away through covers for a glorious boundary.
Drifted onto middle, Brathwaite defends it out with soft hands.
On middle. Blocked out.
A bit quicker, sliding onto middle and leg. Brathwaite stays solid in defense.
Floated up, on off. Brathwaite puts out a big stride forward to defend.
A bit short and wide, this is cut away off the back foot through the point region for a couple of runs.
Quicker one, at 93 kph and around middle and leg. Brathwaite blocks it out.
This is banged in short over off. Jermaine Blackwood hops back and keeps it down on the deck.
A length ball on middle. Kept out on the leg side.
A good short ball, over middle and leg. Blackwood does well to duck under it.
Leg bye! On the pads, Blackwood looks to tuck it away but misses. The ball goes off the pads and rolls towards square leg. They get a leg bye.
Fullish ball, outside off. Left alone by Brathwaite.
Full and on off, punched away towards wide mid off.
A bit of reverse now! Length, around off and tails back in late. Blackwood keeps it out on the leg side.
On middle, blocked out to short mid-wicket.

Close but not close enough! Peach of a delivery first up from Saqib Mahmood. He goes fuller and the ball reverses in late and sharply. Jermaine Blackwood looks to jam it out on the off side but gets hit on the boot. The visitors appeal but umpire Joel Wilson shakes his head. They go for the review and it is clearly boot first. Ball Tracker shows that Blackwood manages to get his foot outside the line of off stump and that saved him. The batters do get a single as well towards covers.
NO BALL! Around off, blcoed out. Mahmood has overstepped and a no ball has been called.
Fullish ball, outside off and this is guided down towards backward point.
A length ball, slanted in from outside off. Brathwaite plays it towards covers.
Pitched up, on off. This is pushed towards mid on.
A length ball, on middle, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Length and slanting on off. Brathwaite hops and blocks it on the deck.
Stokes slants this full ball, on the pads. Brathwaite tickles it to fine leg for one.
Length ball, on middle. Blackwood defends wide of mid on and takes a quick single.
Length again, slanting around off, Brathwaite is solid in his defense.
Short of a length, on middle. Brathwaite stays on the back foot as he tucks it to square leg for a single.
An inswinger, fuller and around off. Brathwaite leans a bit as he blocks it solidly.
Short in length, on middle. Blocked on the leg side.
Fuller and straight on the pads, it is nudged to square leg.
Short of a length, outside off. Brathwaite keeps it out on the off side.
Length and on middle. Brathwaite works it to square leg.
Touch fuller and nipping on off. Brathwaite defends it out. That will be Lunch on Day 3.
Tossed, full and on middle. Blackwood punches back to the bowler.
Fuller again, on middle. This time Blackwood gets on the front foot to defend it.
Slightly short, slower in the air and around off. Blackwood defends it on the off side.
An arm ball, angling on middle. Jermaine keeps it out.
Floate, full and on middle. Blackwood is solid on his front foot defense.
Very full and drifting on middle. Blackwood dead bats it.
On a length, on off. Brathwaite blocks it out.
Fuller and on middle. Brathwaite turns it to the right of mid-wicket for a single.
A length ball, at 129 kph, on off. Blackwood gets a straight bat down to defend.
Length and on middle. Blocked out. A no ball called for overstepping.
Length and around off. Blackwood gets on top of the bounce and taps it on the deck.
Length ball, just outside off. Blackwood wrists it gently in front of mid-wicket and runs across for a quick single.
Length ball, hint of inward shape there, outside off. Brathwaite drops it to covers and will keep the strike.
FOUR! Fifty for Kraigg Brathwaite! His 25th Test match fifty! A hard-fought knock from the skipper. Full and drifting on the pads. Brathwaite sweeps it fine to the fine leg fence.
Flatter, around off. Brathwaite knocks it to covers.
A loopy ball, on off. Brathwaite dabs it to backward point for a single.
Quicker this time, on off. Brathwaite steers it through point but for no run.
Around off, blocked out.
Tossed up, full and on middle, spins after landing but Brathwaite puts a big step forward to block it.
Length ball, slanting around off. Blackwood defends it out.
Fuller and outside off, driven nicely but straight to covers.
Very full and around off. Blackwood works it to covers. A no ball called as Saqib Mahmood overstepped.
Full and on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Fullish and on off. Brathwaite pushes softly to mid on.
Slightly full and on middle. Brathwaite is right behind the line to defend this.
On middle, on a length. Brathwaite tries to work it on the leg side but gets a thick inside edge onto the pads.
An arm ball, fuller and on middle. Blackwood tucks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! This is tossed up, on off. Blackwood hangs on the back foot, plays it very very late and guides it past first slip for a boundary.
Full and on middle. Blocked out.
FOUR! Shorter and on off. Blackwood punches off the back foot through covers. Jonny Bairstow gives a chase, slides near the ropes but fumbles to clear it away. A boundary.
Full and angling on leg. Defended out.
A slider, on middle. Blackwood defends back on the surface.
Length and on off, tucked to mid-wicket.
Full, straight on the pads. Brathwaite flicks it through square leg and will easily get a couple of runs.
On middle. Blocked out.
Full ball, outside off. Brathwaite taps it with soft hands to covers and calls for a quick single. Makes the other end on time.
Full, swinging in, on off. Blackwood plays it late and to mid on.
Length ball, deviating from outside off and hits Blackwood high on the pads as he misses his push. An appeal for LBW but nothing given.
Full, angling on middle. Brathwaite prods and defends.
Flatter, slower and around off. Brathwaite pushes on the back foot to covers.
This one lands on middle and spins away. Brathwaite strides forward and keeps it out.
Flighted, full and on middle. Brathwaite with yet another solid defense.
Angling on the pads, flicked on the leg side for a run.
Very full and on middle. Defended on the front foot.
Length and on middle. Brathwaite turns it to mid-wicket. The ball bounces in front of Dan Lawrence at mid-wicket and he allows a single.
Length and on off. Kept out.

A length ball, on off. Blackwood gets on the front foot to defend but gets a thick outside edge wide of second slip and well away of gully to third man. The ball has no legs to run away and three runs are taken.
Fuller and on off, driven through covers for a couple of runs.
Bangs a short ball, on middle. Brathwaite sits under it.
Length and on off. Brathwaite blocks it out.
Floated, on off. Blackwood lunges and defends.
FOUR! Punished! Shorter and on off, turns away as well. Blackwood punches it hard and through covers for a boundary.
Turns away again, around off, punched to the left of covers and Root makes a good stop. A single taken by the batters.
Tossed up, on off. Brathwaite leans and blocks it.
Very full and on leg, Brathwaite squeezes it out to mid on.
Full again, on middle. Brathwaite works it to mid on.
Hits the deck hard and puts it on a length. Blackwood helps it to deep square leg for a single.

A huge appeal for LBW but that was probably going down the leg side. Length ball, angling on the pads, there is steep bounce as well. Brathwaite looks to flick it but misses and gets rapped well high on the pads.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Pitches it up, on off. Brathwaite caresses it through mid off for a boundary. 150 up for West Indies. A 50-run partnership builds as well.

An appeal for caught behind this time but the replay shows it went off the thigh pad. Length ball, angling down the leg side. Brathwaite looks to flick but misses and it goes off the pads and to the keeper. Good take from Foakes as well.
Full and on middle. Defended out.
Full again. Brathwaite pushes off the inner half of the portion to mid on.
Some start from Root! A flatter ball, drifting around off. Blackwood puts a big stride forward to defend but misses and the keeper collects it quickly. A stifled appeal for caught behind follows.
Around off, pushed through covers for a single.
On middle. Defended on the front foot.
Floated, on middle. Brathwaite prods and blocks it out.
An arm ball, angling on off. Brathwaite plays across the angle to covers for a single.
Tossed up, on a length, on middle. Blackwood knocks it out.
Fuller, swinging back in, on off. Brathwaite works it to square leg.
Gets swing again, on middle. Brathwaite whips it to deep square leg for a single.
Short of a length, slanting on middle. Blackwood tucks it to deep square leg and will take a single.
Fuller and on middle, pushed to mid on.
Down the leg side. Brathwaite shoulders arms to it.
A length ball, at 133 clicks, outside off. Brathwaite with a slight lapse of concentration as he tries to poke it, misses in the end.
Full, quicker and on middle. Blocked out.
Flatter and on off, pushed to covers for a single.
Comes around the wicket, an arm ball, fuller and on middle. Brathwaite digs it out to mid on.
Full and on middle, flicked to square leg for one more.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
FOUR! Root gives width this time, outside off. Blackwood smashes it past cover and bags a boundary.
Fullish and outside off. Brathwaite leans and drives it to covers for a run.
Length and outside off. Blackwood is touch late as he punches it to mid off.
Overpitched delivery, outside off. Blackwood drives it past mid off and gets a couple of runs.
Short in length, outside off. Blackwood mistimes his slap to point.
Length ball, outside off. Blackwood opens the face of the bat and guides it past gully for a brace.
Length and on off. Defended out.
Flatter and on the pads, tucked to the leg side.
Full and on middle. Brathwaite prods to defend.
Shorter and on middle. Brathwaite clears his front leg and pulls it to square leg. No run there.
Darted on the pads, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Another single as this worked to deep mid-wicket.
That is a pacers ball. Root bangs a short ball, on middle. Brathwaite ducks under it.
This is pitched up on off. Blackwood hangs back and defends it out.
Fuller and on off. Blackwood pushes it gently towards mid off.
Close to the off pole, cutting back in just a bit. Jermaine Blackwood awkwardly keeps it out.
Full, on the sixth stump line and this one zips through. Blackwood leaves it alone.
On a nagging length, outside off and keeping a bit low. Blocked out.
In that channel around off and Blackwood makes an assured leave. Maiden!
Fullish delivery, around off and skidding on. Brathwaite keeps it out towards covers.
Good-length, over off. Brathwaite nudges it towards Jonny Bairstow at short cover.
Around the top of off. This is played towards mid on.
A length ball, angled into off. Brathwaite punches it out.
Pitched up, around off. Brathwaite punches it out towards the cover region.
This is slanted into middle and Brathwaite blocks it back to the bowler. Back-to-back maidens for England now.
Leach slides this one down the leg side. Blackwood looks to get a tickle on it but misses.
A bit of turn and bounce. On off, a touch slower and the ball grips. The ball goes off the shoulder of Blackwood's blade and past the slip cordon. Single taken.
On off. Defended out.
Quicker and flatter, around off. Brathwaite hops onto the back foot and pushes it out towards covers.
Pushed through on middle. Blocked.
Slowed up and shorter in length, around off. Brathwaite nudges it towards covers.
On a good length, over off. Blackwood goes on the back foot and pushes it out towards cover.
Length again, around off. Tapped towards covers.
Stokes goes full and on off. Blackwood digs it out towards the bowler.
An attempted bouncer, outside off. Blackwood sways away from the line of the ball.
On a fuller length, outside off and this one comes back in sharply. Blackwood flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length, around off. Jermaine Blackwood punches it towards extra cover.
On the pads, worked towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Fired in at the pads at 93 kph. Jermaine Blackwood goes on the back foot and tucks it 'round the corner for a couple of runs.
Even more quicker, at 95 kph and speared into middle. Blocked.
Around middle, Blackwood defends it out.
On middle again, kept out by Blackwood.
Floated up around middle and leg. Blackwood defends it from deep in his crease.
On a good length, angled in at the body. Brathwaite keeps it down on the leg side.
A bouncer this time, over middle. Brathwaite sits under it.
Around the hips, tucked away to short mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on the pads. Brathwaite works it off his hips and past square leg for a single.
A length ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Length again, around off and this is pushed out towards covers.
Floated up, around middle and leg. This is eased towards mid on.
Quicker one, darted into middle. Kept out by Brathwaite.
Flatter this time, drifting onto the pads. Brathwaite defends it out.
This one slides onto the pads. Brathwaite hangs back and nudges it out.
On middle, Brathwaite strides out to defend.

What a ripper! This is pushed through a bit slower on middle and the ball just grips and turns away sharply. Kraigg Brathwaite has no idea what happened here and the ball misses the off stump by a whisker.
Length and on middle. Blocked out.
Length and angling on middle. Blackwood flicks it to deep square leg and takes a couple of runs. The throw from the deep is good but the running between the wickets was even better.
Short of a length, on the hips, this is hit to square leg for a single.
Length and around off. Brathwaite defends it.
Length ball, extra bounce there, outside off. Brathwaite looks to defend but it goes off the splice through gully for a couple of runs.
Around off, length ball. Blocked out.
FOUR! A length ball, outside off. Brathwaite defends with soft hands and with an angled bat. The ball takes the outside edge and goes past gully for a boundary.

A huge appeal for LBW but not given! An arm ball, fuller and landing on middle, it turns away after pitching. Blackwood looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Might be missing the off stump.
On middle. Blocked out.

Another huge shout for LBW but the umpire is not interested. Angles a flatter ball, down the leg side. Blackwood looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. This time might be missing the leg stump.
Tossed up, full and on off. Blocked out.
This one skids through, on middle. Blackwood defends it very late.
Fuller and on off. Blackwood leans and defends it out. An eventful over from Leach.
Length and on off. Brathwaite taps it with gentle hands to covers and the batters take a quick single.
Length and on middle. Defended out.
Length and on middle, it is pushed to mid-wicket.
This time plays this length ball to covers.
Length ball, outside off. Blackwood punches to mid off.
Leg bye! Angles it on the pads. Blackwood misses his flick. It goes off the pads to square leg for a leg bye.
Shorter and on off, played back to the bowler.
Darted on the pads. Blackwood leans and tickles it past short fine leg for a brace.
A quicker delivery, on middle, worked to square leg.
Flatter and on middle, this is hit to square leg.
On middle, fuller. Blocked out.
Floated, on middle. Blackwood defends on the front foot.
A length ball, around off, not much swing there. Brathwaite blocks it.
Straight ball, length and on middle. Another solid block.
Short of a length, on off. Brathwaite on his toes, punches it past mid off for a run.
Fuller and around off. Blackwood is a touch early as he pushes it back to the bowler.
Length and around off, hint of away shape. Blackwood defends with a horizontal bat.
Jermaine Blackwood is not timing well at the moment. Full and on off, driven to mid off.
A length ball, way outside off. Brathwaite cuts it through point. The ball just slows down near the fence and that gives a chance for Fisher to save a single. Three runs taken.
Around off. Blocked out.

FOUR! Fifty for Jermaine Blackwood! Beautiful knock from the vice-captain so far and he will love to continue here. Short and way outside off. Blackwood cuts it hard this time and through point for a boundary.
Outside off again. Left alone.
This one lands on off and there is good turn and bounce on offer. Blackwood prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Again sharp turn! Tossed up, on off. Blackwood misses his defense again. That will be Tea on Day 3.
FOUR! A loosener to start with from Chris Woakes. Overpitched outside off and shaping away. Kraigg Brathwaite stands tall and creams it through covers for a boundary. The 200 is up for the Windies.
A length ball, outside off. Brathwaite doesn't play at it.
Length again, a bit closer to the off pole this time. Brathwaite makes an easy leave.
FOUR! Brilliant timing from the skipper and the 100 partnership is up. A half volley on off, Brathwaite drives it right back past the bowler and picks up a boundary down to long off.
Around off, Brathwaite looks to drives again but gets an inside edge onto the pads this time.
Around the top of off, tucked away towards mid-wicket.
A length ball, around middle. Blackwood hangs back and pushes it out towards mid-wicket for a single.
A touch slower, around the top of off. Brathwaite keeps it out.
Angled on the pads, tucked away to fine leg for a run.
Easy two! A bit too straight and Jermaine Blackwood works it through square leg for a couple of runs.
Fisher bangs it in a little bit shorter with a scrambled seam and outside off. Blackwood hops and makes the leave.
On off, blocked out.
A bit more intent from Woakes and he hits the length hard, around leg stump. Brathwaite looks to work it behind but gets hit on the thigh pads.
Early call for the single and they get it with ease. On the pads, nudged away to the right of square leg for a quick run.
Woakes is bowling a bit too straight at the moment. Around the hips, tucked away to deep square leg for one more.
On a good length, over off. Brathwaite goes deep in his crease to make the block.
Much fuller, on the sixth stump line. Brathwaite leaves it alone.
On off, solidly defended towards covers by Brathwaite.
Pitched up, around the off stump. Blackwood defends it of the front foot.
Around off, punched away to cover-point.
This is pushed well wide of the off stump. No need to play at that.
On off, Blackwood with another solid front foot defensive shot.
Length, on off. Blackwood looks to turn it leg side but gets squared up a bit.
A rare play and a miss from Jermaine Blackwood. Good-length on a line around off. Blackwood misses the punch off the back foot and gets beaten past the outside edge.
Flatter and on off, tapped to cover-point.
Nicely drifted into middle and leg. Brathwaite strides out to defend.
This is is pushed through a bit quicker, at 91 kph and on middle. Brathwaite blocks it out.
Darted into middle and leg. Brathwaite keeps it out.
Turning away from around the pads, Brathwaite  makes a watchful block.
This is floated up, a bit outside off. Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Length ball, hint of shape there. Blackwood blocks it out.
FOUR! A length ball, width given, outside off. Blackwood square cuts it in the gap, through point. Saqib Mahmood gives a chase but to no avail.
FOUR! Length and on the pads. Blackwood flicks it aerially and to square leg for a boundary.
Length ball, moving back in around off. Blackwood punches back to the bowler.
On middle, pushed to mid on.
A yorker this time, on middle. Blackwood digs it out nicely.
Short and outside off, cut to deep point for a single.
Flatter and on off. Punched to covers.
Leach keeps it tight, around off, pushed back.
Tossed up, full and on off. Blackwood looks to push but gets an outside edge to point for a single.
On middle. Brathwaite prods and defends this out.
Full and on middle. Brathwaite leans and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Length and on middle, Blocked out.
Angles a length ball, on middle. Jermaine works it to mid-wicket.
A slower ball, on middle. Blackwood eases it to mid-wicket.
Touch fuller and on middle. Blackwood defends it out.
Another solid block from Jermaine Blackwood.
Length and outside off. Blackwood punches on the up and to covers.
Fuller ball, slanting on the pads. Brathwaite flicks it past square leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR!  Fullish and on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite on drives it well wide of mid on for a boundary.
Outside off. Brathwaite pushes softly to covers.
Full and angling on middle. Brathwaite plays with good hands but straight to mid on.
Again times this full ball well but finds mid on.
Length ball, outside off. Brathwaite punches it as he gets on his toes but fails to pierce through at covers.
A full ball, on the pads. Blackwood misses his sweep and it goes off the pads to square leg.
On the pads again. Blackwood keeps it out on the leg side.
Flatter and on leg. Defended out.
A flatter ball, on middle, this lands and turns away. Blackwood closes his bat face as he looks to work it on the leg side but gets a leading edge through point for a couple of runs.
Tossed up, on middle, blocked out.
Full and angling down. Brathwaite tucks it to short leg.
A length ball, on middle. Blackwood hits it on the tup, to the right of mid on and picks up a single.
Not perfectly timed. Full and straight, Brathwaite punches it back past the bowler for a run.
On middle, pushes out by Blackwood.
Nicely bowled! On a driving length, in that channel around off and there is a bit of shape here for Mahmood. Jermaine Blackwood looks to drive it through covers but gets beaten past the outside edge.

NO BALL! Oh no! The sheer agony and Saqib Mahmood looks distraught. Mahmood bowls a signature inswinging yorker on off stump. Jermaine Blackwood is deep in his crease and just as he looks to jam it out, the ball sneaks under the willow and hits the base of off stump. Mahmood celebrates as he thinks he's got his maiden Test wicket but hold on, the third umpire signals that Mahmood has overstepped. Blackwood breathes a sigh of relief and the replay confirms that it is indeed a clear no ball.

Mahmood is buzzing here! Fuller, around off and the ball just nips back in sharply and way too much. Jermaine Blackwood leaves it on line but the ball was a lot closer to the off stump than Blackwood thought.
Good-length, angled onto the pads. Blackwood turns it off his hips onto the leg side and picks up a single.
On middle. Blocked out.
Shorter this time, at the stumps. Blackwood pushes it back to the bowler off the back foot.
Fuller this time, on off. Blackwood defends it out.
Full and on middle. Blackwood with another solid block.
This one slides on with the arm. Blackwood backs away and pushes it towards cover.
Around the pads, Jermaine Blackwood tickles it fine, past leg slip and comes back for the second with ease.
Back of a length, on the body. Brathwaite works it off the back foot towards square leg.
Good-length, over off. Brathwaite stays solid in defsnse. He still remains on 97.
Now he does get the single. Full and straight, flicked away to wide mid on for a run.
Fullish ball, around off. This is worked towards mid-wicket by Blackwood.
Angled into middle and leg, Blackwood fails to get it away leg side.
On the hips, Jermaine Blackwood hops and tucks it away towards backward square leg. The batters push hard for two and get it with ease in the end.
This is pushed through on middle. Brathwaite defends it out.

A deft touch from the skipper and Kraigg Brathwaite brings up a well-compiled century. Flatter, around off. Brathwaite goes deep in his crease and opens the face of the bat to guide it past backward point for a couple of runs. This has been a monumental effort in concentration from Brathwaite and he gets a round of applause from everyone in the crowd.
Uppish! On the pads, Brathwaite plays a half=sweep which goes towards backward square leg.
A little bit of flight, around off. Brathwaite plays it with the spin towards covers.
Full and around off. Brathwaite leans in to make the block.
Outside off and turning away, there's a bit of an extra bounce as well. Brathwaite hangs back and steers it on the off side.
This is slanted down the leg side. Blackwood looks to flick but misses.
Stokes goes full and straight, trying to sneak one past the bat. Blackwood stays solid in defense.
Around the top of off, kicks off the pitch a bit. Jermaine Blackwood does well to fend it off on the off side.
Good-length, over middle. Blackwood defends it back onto the deck.

Around off, blocked back to the bowler. Jonny Bairstow is as chirpy as ever in the field. You can hear him push his side as he says 'still 270 behind guys, come on bang, bang.' He wants the bowlers to stay motivated here and that's the energy they need.
This is outside off. Blackwood doesn't play at it.
FOUR! Freebie! Short and wide outside off. Brathwaite cuts and beats point with ease and collect a boundary for himself.
Tossed up, on middle. Brathwaite dead bats it.
Fuller and on middle. Brathwaite blocks it on the front foot.
Touch fuller, angling on middle. Another solid block from Brathwaite.
Slightly short and on middle. Brathwaite rocks back and defends it.
A maiden over! Flatter and on off. Brathwaite sees it out on the off side.
A short ball, on middle. Blackwood bends his back and lets it through.
Length and on middle. Blackwood gets behind the line to dead bat it.
Short and down the leg side. Blackwood sits under it.
On a length, on off. Blackwood offers a dead bat to it.
Length ball, around off and steep bounce there. Blackwood pushes it slightly uppishly and back to the bowler.
On middle. Blocked out.
Flatter and on middle. Brathwaite defends it.
Shorter and angling across, outside off. Brathwaite with deft touch, plays it to third man for a couple of runs.
Short ball, angling on leg. Brathwaite is not interested to play that and allows the ball to meet the pads.
Tossed up, on off. Defended.
On the pads, Brathwaite keeps it out.
This one spins into the right-hander, around leg. Brathwaite is rock solid in his defense.
Stokes continues to bowl short but Blackwood continues to leave it alone.
Angles it on the pads, flicked wide of square leg for a couple of runs.
Fuller and angling on middle. Blackwood defends with an angled bat to point.
Full and on middle. Blackwood gets a straight bat down to defend.
FOUR! Short again from Stokes but this time it was well outside off. Blackwood latches on it and hits it over cover-point for a boundary.
Full and on off. Blackwood is squared up a bit as he tries to defend this. It goes off the splice to point.
Flatter and turing on the pads. Brathwaite is happy to take it on the pads. The impact is always the key here.
Again, angling on the pads. Brathwaite shoulders arms to it.
Flatter and on middle. Brathwaite blocks it.
Four byes! Flatter, well outside leg and turning in. Brathwaite tries to pad it away but misses, the keeper misses to collect and it goes behind to the fence.
Darted on the pads. Brathwaite tucks it to square leg.
Full, outside leg and spinning onto the pads. Brathwaite pads it away.
Stokes pushes this one full and at the pads. Jermaine Blackwood pushes it out well in front of square on the leg side for a brace.
FOUR! Two short mid-wickets are kept in place and still Blackwood finds the gap. Floated up on the pads, Blackwood with a lovely on drive through the in field and picks up a boundary.
On off. Blocked.

A bit of aggression shown here by the bowler and the batter. Full, around off and driven straight towards mid off. Jermaine Blackwood has a clear shout of 'No' to his partner but Stokes mimics him and Blackwood keeps shouting 'no' in response.
Stokes keeps chirping back to the batter. Full and straight, dug out on the off side and this has brought the crowd alive. Stokes needs to be careful here.
A dot to finish and Ben Stokes just can't control himself. On off, blocked out. Stokes is peppering Blackwood with his words and now it's getting a bit too far.
Leach comes from over the wicket and bowls it shorter, around leg. Brathwaite keeps it down on the leg side off the back foot.
Flatter, around leg stump. Brathwaite blocks it off.
Outside the leg stump, Brathwaite looks to leave it alone but ends up padding it away.
Leach goes back to 'round the wicket and drifts it into middle. Brathwaite nudges it onto the leg side.

Half a chance for Alex Lees at short leg but he's never getting that one. On the pads, Brathwaite presses forward and flicks it uppishly to the right of short leg and the bowler lets out a sigh of agony. The batters get a single as well.
This time past leg slip! Nicely drifted onto the pads, Blackwood looks to flicks it behind with soft hands but gets an inside edge past the diving fielder at leg slip for a single.
Chris Woakes keeps up his record of starting a new spell in this series with a loosener. Floiated up on the pads, Jermaine Blackwood clips it through mid-wicket and picks up an easy three.
On the money this time from Woakes. Brathwaite with another solid defensive block.
Around middle and leg, dabbed down on the leg side.
An off cutter from Woakes, full and on off. Brathwaite flicks it towards silly mid on.
On off, wristed away to the man at mid-wicket.
A length ball, around off. This is tapped straight to the fielder at cover-point.
Floated up, full and on leg stump. Jermaine Blackwood makes room and flicks it through mid-wicket. Joe Root gives chase and keeps it down to a single.
On off, blocked out.
Drifted into middle. Brathwaite stays solid in defense.
Ripper! Slowed up, on a length and close to the off stump. The ball grips, turns and bounces a bit extra. Brathwaite looks to push at it but gets beaten past the outside edge.
At the stumps, kept out by Brathwaite.
Around off, pushed out onto the off side.
Shorter in length, over off. Blackwood defends it back onto the deck.
NPitched up, around off. Blackwood strokes it firmly towards covers.
Around the hips, tucked away towards short mid-wicket.
Leg bye! A length ball, sliding onto the pads. Blackwood looks to flick but misses. The ball goes off the pads and behind square on the leg side. They get a leg bye.
Pitched up on off. Brathwaite presses forward to make the block.
Slower and sliding down the leg side. Brathwaite misses the flick.
Tossed up, on off. Blackwood gets back to defend.
Very full and on middle. Blackwood squeezes it to mid on.
Full again, angling on the pads. Blackwood tucks it to square leg for a single.
Floated, on middle. Blocked out.
Slightly short and on off. Brathwaite cuts it past point for a brace.
Tossed up, sliding around leg. Brathwaite prods to defend it out.
Length ball, on off. Blackwood taps it back to Woakes. The keeper is standing up to the stumps.
Full and on middle, flicked to deep square leg for a couple of runs. He moves into the 90s now.

FOUR! A length ball, slanting around the 4th stump channel. Blackwood defends with soft hands. It goes of the outside edge and to the left of first slip for a boundary. No chance for the fielder to even stop it.
Around off. Blocked out.
Around off, length and Jermaine works it to covers.
On middle, this is hit to square leg for one.
Length and on middle. Blackwood clips it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs. He is three runs away from a century now.
Shorter and on off. Blackwood plays it late and defends it down.
Flatter and on middle. Blackwood flicks it well and to deep square leg. The fielder runs to his left and stops it. The batters take two runs.
An appeal for LBW but not given! Flatter and down the leg side. Blackwood misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. Was sliding well down.
On middle. Flicked to square leg where Jonny Bairstow makes a good stop.

Century for Jermaine Blackwood! His 3rd in Test cricket! There is a sigh of relief as he celebrates the landmark. A fist pump in the air, removes the helmet and soaks all the applause from the crowd. On to the ball. It was around off. Blackwood dabs it to point for a single.
A slider, angling on the pads, nudged to square leg.
Drift and spin for Dan Lawrence, Tossed up and on middle. Blackwood keeps it out.
Full and on noff. Blackwood stretches forward to defend it.
Short, well outside off. Blackwood covers his stumps and lets it through.
Tossed up, on off, pushed back to Dan.
Flighted ball, on middle. Blackwood turns it to square leg and will keep the strike.
Short and on middle. Jermaine whacks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Defended out.

Is that a chance? Yes, Ben Foakes has missed a stumping chance. Full and angling down the leg side. Brathwaite strides forward to defend but misses and the ball goes to the keeper. Brathwaite was well out but Foakes failed to grab it and the ball hits his pads. A chance goes begging for England.
On middle, fuller and this one is blocked out.
Another solid block from Brathwaite.
Full and angling on the pads. Brathwaite tucks it to mid-wicket.

OUT! LBW! Well, what happened here? A moment of real lapse in concentration from Jermaine Blackwood and he has to walk back. This is nicely flighted, on a length and around off. The ball turns in and Blackwood shoulders arms. He gets trapped in plumb in front and the finger is raised. It is reviewed but Blackwood doesn't seem confident. No shot was offered so impact doesn't matter. Ball Tracker shows that it is hitting middle stump and Blackwood is livid with himself. Dan Lawrence has done it again as he gets the wicket of yet another centurion and its the end of a brilliant knock from Blackwood.
Howout: lbw b Dan Lawrence

Commentary: Floated up, around off. Joseph caresses it towards point.
Nicely bowled! Looped up, full and around off. Joseph looks to drive it through covers but gets completely undone in flight.
Not holding back Alzarri Joseph but that's risky. Shorter on off, Joseph hangs back and looks to pull it away but mistimes it towards mid-wicket.
On off, Joseph strides out to defend. Much better from him.
Floated up, around off. This is kept out on the off side. A wicket-maiden for Dan Lawrence.
Drifted onto middle, Brathwaite strides out and blocks it out with soft hands.
Flatter, around off. Brathwaite nudges it on the off side.
This is drifted onto the pads. Blocked.
Leach pulls back the length a bit and bowls it on off. Brathwaite goes on the back foot to defend.
On middle, kept out yet again.
Drifted into middle, defended off the front foot. Maiden!
Turning in from around off, Joseph gets an inside edge past short leg.
On a driving length, outside off. Alzarri Joseph pushes it past silly point.
A tad shorter, on middle. Joseph rocks back and keeps it out.
On off, stroked away on the off side.
Nicely bowled! Flighted, a bit fuller and around off. The ball turns in and Joseph makes a watchful block.
Close to the off pole and this one drifts in but doesn't spin much. Joseph looks to block but the ball slides past the outside edge. Yet another maiden over for England.
On off, pushed towards short mid off.
This is skidded through on middle. Brathwaite is a little late in his front foot defense.
On middle, defended under the eye line by Brathwaite.
This is pushed through on middle and leg. Brathwaite dead-bats it.
Flatter and on middle. Brathwaite hangs back to defend.
Floated on middle and leg, Brathwaite blocks it off with ease.
Flighted, outside off and inviting the drive. Alzarri Joseph plays a loose shot as he looks to drive, gets beaten past the outside edge.
Shorter and on off. Kept out by Joseph.
Around off, dabbed down past point but the batters do not take the run.
FOUR! A half-volley around off and with all the fielders in and around the bat, Alzarri Joseph takes on the cover drive. He creams it to the cover fence and gets off the mark.
On off, blocked out.

NOT OUT! Drama on the final delivery of Day 3 but Alzarri Joseph survives. This is flighted again, on a length and on off. The ball turns in sharply. Joseph strides out to block but misses and gets rapped on the pads. The fielder at silly point pouches it and they all go up in unison. The review is taken and there is no spike on UltraEdge. The lbw is also checked but the ball is going miles down the leg side. Alzarri Joseph negotiates the final over and that will be curtains on Day 3.

FOUR! Runs straightaway on Day 4! A loosener from Matthew Fisher, on the pads. Kraigg Brathwaite helps it on it's way to fine leg. Ben Foakes dives to his left but could not stop the ball from racing away.
Length ball, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite nudges it to mid-wicket.
Fuller in length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Short ball to Alzarri Joseph, on middle. Alzarri Joseph doesn't offer any shot and takes a blow on the gloves.
On a length, on middle. Joseph works it to short mid-wicket.
On a length, leg-lined. Alzarri Joseph tries to tuck but the ball brushes his pads and rolls to the keeper.
Loopy ball to start with, down leg. Kraigg Brathwaite hangs back and clips it to deep square leg. Calls for two and gets it easily.
Fuller length, on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it on the leg side.
Tossed up nicely, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it from the crease.
Loopy ball, on off, turning away. Kraigg Brathwaite taps it to the off side.
Full and on middle, kept out by Kraigg Brathwaite.
Floats it up, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite lunges forward. Defends it off the outer half to backward point. Just 2 runs off Leach's over!
Back of a length, on off. Alzarri Joseph stands tall and meets it with a dead bat.
FOUR! Lovely stroke! Length ball, outside off. Alzarri Joseph drives it behind point. Zak Crawley gives it a chase but the ball wins the race.
On a length, on off. Alzarri Joseph keeps it out.
An effort ball from Matthew Fisher, on off. Alzarri Joseph sways away from the line and lets it go.
Short ball again, on middle. Alzarri Joseph ducks under it.
Good-length ball, around the fourth stump channel. Alzarri Joseph watches it closely and decides to leave it alone.
Tossed up, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it well.
Flatter and quicker, at 88 kph, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it out.
Full and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite prods and defends it off the outer half to backward point.
Flatter, on the pads. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend. The ball goes off the inside edge and hits him on the pads. Lobs to backward square leg for a single. 300 up for West Indies!
On off, blocked out.
Loopy ball, on middle. Joseph blocks it watchfully.
Short ball, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite sits under it.
Goes full this time, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it to mid off.
On a good length, around off, some extra bounce on that one. Kraigg Brathwaite is taken aback by that but manages to fend it on the leg side.
Back of a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite hops and offers a straight bat.
Short ball again, on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite ducks underneath.
FOUR! Cut away in the gap! Short of a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite stays deep and cuts it hard behind point. That went off like a bullet. A boundary!
Loopy ball, on off. Alzarri Joseph punches it towards covers off the back foot.
On off, blocked out.
Floats it up, outside off. Alzarri Joseph fends it away to the off side.
Flatter and quicker, on off. Alzarri Joseph keeps it out.
Absolute ripper! Tossed up, outside off, spinning away. Alzarri Joseph prods and looks to defend. But the ball goes past the outside edge and just goes over the middle stump.
Fuller, around off. Joseph blocks it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite slashes it through cover-point for a brace.
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite taps it towards covers off the back foot.
FOUR! Flashed away! Back of a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite throws his hands and cuts it to third man for a boundary.
Angling in a length ball, on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite stands up on his toes and pushes it to cover.
Width on offer again, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite steers it through cover-point and gets two this time.
Full and on the pads, Alzarri Joseph defends it to short leg.
Tossed up, spinning away from off. Alzarri Joseph hangs back to defend but the ball zips past the outside edge.
On middle, kept out.
Quicker delivery, on off. Alzarri Joseph stays back and defends.
Full and on off, Alzarri Joseph lunges and blocks it out.
A maiden! On leg, Alzarri Joseph works it to mid-wicket.
Fuller, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it to mid off.
Short of a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite hops and tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, on off. Alzarri Joseph gets behind the ball and defends it out.
Short ball, outside off that dies on the way. Alzarri Joseph sways away from the line.
Back of a length, on middle. Played back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, on off. Alzarri Joseph blocks it solidly. He is supporting Kraigg Brathwaite well here. Perfectly playing the role of a night watchman.
Full and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out pressing forward.
On off, Kraigg Brathwaite prods and pushes it to mid off.
Flatter, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite slashes it to deep cover for a run.
Full and on the pads, Alzarri Joseph clips it off the pads past leg gully for a single.

How did that miss? So, so close! Tossed up nicely, spinning away from leg, Kraigg Brathwaite presses forward to block. The ball goes past the bat and just goes past the off pole. Whiskers away from hitting! Kraigg Brathwaite is very lucky there!
An arm ball, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it out.
Loopy ball, outside off. Alzarri Joseph plays it to sweeper cover for one.
Floats it up, on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Shorter length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite punches it to long on for a single.
Floats it up, on off. Alzarri Joseph is solid in his defence.
On off, spinning in. Alzarri Joseph blocks it from the crease.
Tossed up, outside off. Alzarri Joseph throws his bat and gets an outside edge to third man for a brace.
On middle, defended.
Tosses it up, fuller and on middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Shorter and outside off, this is slapped through covers for one.
Misreads the length there! Goes back to a ball which he should be playing forward too. Joseph looks to defend but it goes off the outer half to point.
This time he goes back to the right ball and guides it to point.
On middle, defended.
Three more! Runs continue to flow! Fuller and outside off, this is driven through covers for three.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
Another one tossed up on off, kept out.
A little flatter this time and around off, Joseph pushes it to covers.
Another one tossed up on off, pushed to cover again.
Flatter and on middle, this one turns back in. Joseph tries to leave but it hits the pad.
Tossed up and on middle, defended.
Gives it air and lands it on the stumps, it is kept out.
That has turned a long way! This lands outside off and spins away a long way. Left alone.
On middle, tossed up on middle, it is pushed back to the bowler.
On the stumps, kept out.
Flatter and on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite plays it to covers.
Slower through the air and on off, Joseph defends.
This is flatter but shorter, it lands outside off and turns back in. Alzarri Joseph goes back and defends.
On the stumps, kept out again.
Fired on the stumps yet again, kept out.
On middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.

SIX! Over the fence! Catch it was the cry but he had hit that well. Really good, a bad ball and Alzarri Joseph does not miss out. He rocks back to this short one and hammers it over the square leg fence.
EDGY FOUR! Frustrating for England! Length and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite opens the face of the bat but it goes more off the edge between gully and first slip for a boundary.
Good length on off, closer to the off pole, defended.
Angled into the off pole from wide of the crease, it is pushed to covers.
On middle, blocked.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite stands tall and defends it.
Bowls the one that comes in with the angle, it is kept out.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On the stumps, Joseph defends it nicely. Absolutely nothing from the wicket for the bowler.
Yet again, this is tossed up on middle, goes on with the arm. Joseph defends.
Too easy! Angled into middle, lands and comes slow off the surface. Joseph plays it out.
This one is fired on middle, Joseph stays back and keeps it out.
A bumper, the batter has enough time to get under the ball. That is how slow the surface is.
