Edgy runs again! Fifty-run stand up and this partnership is really frustrating for England. Length and on off, Brathwaite plays inside the line, it goes off the outer half towards backward point for two.
Shorter and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends.
Angled into the pads, Kraigg Brathwaite works it to mid-wicket.
The awayswinger, it is well outside off though, left alone.
A yorker, fuller and on middle, this is jammed out to mid off.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
Tossed up and on middle, kept out.
A little too short, comes slow off the surface. Defended.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Shorter and outside off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Gives it air and lands it on middle, kept out easily.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a sharp, sharp catch! It flew to him. Finally, England manage to get the nightwatchman out who we feel has done his job. Not the best of deliveries though to dismiss him. It is short and wide outside off, Alzarri Joseph throws his bat at it, it goes more off the outer half and quickl to Dan Lawrence at gully. He takes it nicely. Windies trail by another 171. Jason Holder walks out to bat.
Howout: c Dan Lawrence b Ben Stokes

Commentary: Good length and on off, Holder keeps it out.
Shorter and on off, a little bit of extra bounce, Holder does well to guide it to point.

FOUR! Off the mark in a streaky manner and Stokes is not at all happy with that. He runs in, lands it on a length and around off, it lands and moves away. Holder looks to defend, he does so with soft hands. It goes off the outside edge between first slip and a widish second slip fielder and down to the third man fence.
Good length and on off, defended. Good from Stokes, making the batter play almost everything.
Yet again causing problems! Length and on off, this one jags back in. Holder looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
On middle, kept out.
Angled into the stumps, defended.
Loopy ball and on middle, KB is solid in defense.
Yet again floats it up and on off, played back to the bowler.
Good, tidy stuff from Leach! On middle, Kraigg Brathwaite manages to keep it out.

A good nut to end a maiden over! On middle, this lands and turns away. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend with soft hands, it goes more off the outside edge but lands well short of first slip. Now Kraigg Brathwaite has faced 400 balls.
FOUR! That is a wonderful stroke! Fuller and on off, Holder shows the full face of the bat and strokes it through mid off. Boundary.
Solid! Shortens the length and lands it on off, kept out.
Angled into middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Relentless stuff from Stokes! Makes the batter play again by bowling it on off, blocked.
And again, attacks the stumps, it is pushed to mid off.
Well left! Another one on a length and just outside off, left alone.
On off, this is kept out.
On middle, this is kept out.
On off, this is defended.
Flatter and on the stumps, kept out.
On off, defended.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Outside off, this is guided towards point for one.
A bumper, that does not bounce a lot. Brathwaite ducks, it goes just over the body.
Angled into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Fuller, gets it to shape back in from outside off, Holder looks to drive but it goes off the inner half on the leg side.
BEATEN! Plays at one he did not need to! This is well outside off, Holder probably was worried about the incoming angle. He has a poke at it but is beaten.
On middle, defended.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Floats it up on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Floats it up on off, it is driven to mid off.
Gives it air and lands it on the stumps, kept out.
Loopy ball on off, blocked.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Beaten again but don't think it would have carried! Length and outside off, this one holds its line. Holder plays at it, it goes off the outside edge and lands well short of the keeper.
Extra bounce now! On a length and on off, this one takes off. Holder looks to defend but it hits him on the glove.

Edgy run! Frustrating for Stokes who is causing problems for Holder. Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Holder looks to defend but it goes off the outer half, lands short of first slip who gets a hand and it goes behind for one.
Now goes wide of the crease and angles it into middle, blocked.
Bangs it short and on middle, ducked under.
An arm ball, on middle. Jason Holder blocks it out.
Slower through the air, on off. Jason Holder strides forward to block.
Loopy ball, on off. Holder outside-edges it to bakcward point trying to defend.
This is nudged to mid-wicket.
Full and on off, kept out.
Floats it up, on middle. Holder defends that easily. A maiden!
Fuller in length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it straight down the ground. The ball goes on to disturb the stumps at the bowler's end.
Length ball, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite lets it sail through.
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite covers the line and defends.
Short ball, on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite sits under it.
Fuller, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it to cover.
On a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite lifts his bat and lets it go. Another maiden for Stokes!
Tossed up, outside off. Jason Holder hangs back and defends.
Full and on off, blocked out.
Flatter, full and on leg, Jason Holder whips it to wide of mid on.
Full, on middle. Kept out.
On off, Jason Holder prods and defends it out.
Short and on off, Jason Holder defends it to the off side. Three back-to-back maidens for England!
Fuller in length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it watchfully.
Short of a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite hops and plays it to cover.
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite knocks it back to the bowler.
Length, on leg. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it to square leg.
Length ball, on leg. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it uppishly but well wide of Dan Lawrence at short mid-wicket.
Full and on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
On off, Jason Holder strides forward and blocks.
Full and outside off, Jason Holder lunges forward and blocks it out.
On off, kept out.
Tossed up, on middle. Jason Holder defends it easily.
Short and on middle, defended watchfully.
Floats it up, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler. No run has been scored in the last 5 overs!
Short of a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it off the back foot.
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite covers the line and knocks it in front of mid off.
Fuller in length, on leg. Driven to mid on.
Length ball, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out watchfully.
Another maiden! On off, this is defended easily.
First run after 6 maidens! Loopy ball, outside off. Jason Holder looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge past slip for a single.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
Full again, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite stays solid in defence.
Outside off, driven towards covers.
Full and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite guides it to point.
Short and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite slashes it past point for a brace. 350 up for West Indies!
Length ball, outside off. Jason Holder dabs it down to third man for a run.
Short of a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite knocks it back to the bowler.
Length ball, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it to short leg off the back foot.
Length ball, on off. Pushed towards covers.
Touch fuller, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite taps it to point.
Length ball, on middle and leg, Kraigg Brathwaite covers the line and defends it on the leg side. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Length ball to begin with, on middle and leg. Jason Holder clips this uppishly to mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a joyous occasion for Saqib Mahmood as he picks up his maiden Test wicket and it has come right after the break for England. Saqib Mahmood bowls this little short this time, on middle. Jason Holder looks to heave it away but miscues it high up in the air towards the mid on region. Matthew Fisher there waits and waits, settles himself under the skier and pouches it with both the hands. A really good catch by him and Saqib Mahmood is pumped up. Spectacular catch from Matthew Fisher and England just wicket away from getting into the tail enders.
Howout: c Matthew Fisher b Saqib Mahmood

Commentary: On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends.
Length ball and Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it on the leg side for a single.
Length, on leg. Joshua Da Silva prods to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Good-length ball, outside off. Joshua Da Silva cuts it past point to get off the mark. Two runs!
On middle, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the back foot.
Full and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Outside off, cut away to sweeper cover for one.
Joshua Da Silva flicks this full ball on the leg side for a single.
Outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite strides forward but decides to leave it alone.
Full and on off, kept out.
Good length, on off. Joshua Da Silva hangs back and defends it under his eyes.
Full and on off, tapped to the off side.

NOT OUT! Good-length ball, on middle, angling in. Joshua Da Silva hops and looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the front pad. England appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Joshua Da Silva opts for a review after having a chat with his skipper, Kraigg Brathwaite. UltraEdge shows that there was a spike as the ball passes the bat. Inside edge saves Joshua Da Silva and the on-field decision is overturned. West Indies retain their review as well.
Fullish, on off. Defended down the pitch.
Outside off, on a good length. Joshua Da Silva leaves it alone.
Angling in a length ball, on middle. Joshua Da Silva shuffles across and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on middle. KB defends it out.
Outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite taps it to point.
Loopy ball, outside off. Left alone by Kraigg Brathwaite.
Short and on off, punched off the back foot towards mid off.
Floats it up, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite works it through covers for a single.
Full and on leg, Joshua Da Silva defends it to short leg.
On a length, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite dabs it down to deep point for a single. He moves to 149!
NO BALL!Touch fuller, on off. Joshua Da Silva covers the line and defends. Saqib Mahmood has overstepped and will have to reload.
Short ball, on middle. Joshua Da Silva pulls it to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, on off. Joshua Da Silva taps it to point.
Length ball, on off. Joshua Da Silva steps out and pushes it to mid on.
Length ball, outside off. Joshua Da Silva strides forward and keeps it out.
Back of a length, on off. Joshua Da Silva hops and defends it back to the bowler.

150 for Kraigg Brathwaite! Wonderful achievement for him! A fantastic innings and he is leading from the front. Gets to the milestone by clipping this full ball to mid on for a quick single. He raises his bat and soaks all the applause.

NOT OUT! Loopy delivery, on leg. Joshua Da Silva rocks back and looks to tuck it on the leg side but gets thudded on the pads. The ball lobs in the air to leg slip. England appeal for a catch but the umpire says no. They seem very confident and England go for a review. Nothing on UltraEdge and the umpire checks for an LBW as well. The impact is outside leg and the original decision stands. A poor review by England!
Flighted delivery, full and on off. Joshua Da Silva blocks.
On off, chopped to point.
On middle and leg, Joshua Da Silva keeps it out.
Joshua Da Silva gets forward and defends this loopy ball to the off side.
Length ball down leg, stays low. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to glance but misses. Ben Foakes does well to dive to his left and stop the ball.
Short ball, on middle. The ball this time bounces a little too much. Kraigg Brathwaite does very well to sway away from the line.
Short of a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite chops it to point.
Fuller, attacking the stumps. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it to mid on.
Short ball again, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite sits under it.
Width on offer, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite cuts it hard but can't beat the point fielder.
Length ball, on off. Joshua Da Silva gets behind the line and knocks it to mid on with a straight bat.
Yet again looks to attack the front pad. Joshua blocks it.
Bends his back on this one, gets some extra bounce after it lands on a length. Joshua does well to defend by taking one hand off the handle.
Another one on a length and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Fuller and on off, Joshua pushes it to mid off.
On the fuller side, Joshua shows the full face of the bat and strokes it to mid on.
Gets this to tail back in nicely from around off, this is worked through square leg for one.
An appeal but the umpire is quick to wave it off! On the pads, Joshua looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Solid! Gets it to tail back in from outside off. Defended.
Just outside off, no movement this time. Left alone.
Probably went for the yorker but ends up bowling a full toss on middle, this is flicked to mid-wicket.
Good change in length there. Bangs it short and on middle, ducked under.
Good length and on off, kept out.
Goes fuller this time and on off, Brathwaite pushes it to covers.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Length and on off, Joshua plays it to covers.

FOUR! Edged but wide! That is bad luck for Stokes. On an another day, would have gone to hand. Full and wide outside off, Joshua goes after it. It goes off the outside edge and wide of second slip for a boundary.
Angled into the pads, Stokes works it to mid-wicket.
Going down leg! Fisher gets this one to shape back in late from around off. Brathwaite misses the flick and gets hit on the pads.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Fuller, this one shapes back in nicely. It is played to mid on.
Angled into the pads, this is worked behind square on the leg side for one.
On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
A short one to end, Brathwaite ducks under it.
Swing straightaway! Good length, outside off, shaping away. Joshua Da Silva leaves it alone.
Length ball, outside off, Joshua Da Silva shoulders arms.
Short of a length, angling in from outside off. Joshua Da Silva pushes it to backward point.
Full and on the pads. Joshua Da Silva flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, shaping away, outside off. Left alone.
Good length but well outside off. An easy leave for Kraigg Brathwaite.
Down leg, Joshua Da Silva lets it be.
Fullish, outside off. Joshua Da Silva reaches out for it and drives it through point for a couple of runs.
Outside off, shaping away. Joshua Da Silva offers no shot.
Short of a length, outside off. Joshua Da Silva taps it to point for a single.
Length ball, outside off, shaping in. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Fuller, outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite plays it to mid off.
Length ball, with a hint of away swing on off. Joshua Da Silva blocks it to the off side.
This one swings a lot! Length ball, outside off, swinging a long way further. Joshua Da Silva leaves it alone and Ben Foakes does well to dive to his right and grab the ball.
On a length, on off. Joshua Da Silva stands tall and defends.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Joshua Da Silva clips it to deep square leg for a brace.
Peach! Good-length ball, outside off, holds the line as well after landing. Joshua Da Silva looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Outside off, driven towards covers.
On off, Kraigg Brathwaite plays it to cover.
Length ball, leg-lined. Kraigg Brathwaite is surprised by the bounce and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Fuller, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it crisply but straight to extra cover.
Short of a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and fends it away to the off side for one.
Length ball, shaping in from outside off. Joe Root shoulders arms.
Length, on middle. Joshua Da Silva pokes it to point.
Length ball, on leg. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
Once again down leg. Joshua Da Silva glances it to fine legfor a single.
Full and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it out.

FOUR! Stokes is shaking his head! He is doing everthing right but things are not going his way. Short of a length, outside off. Induces an outside edge as Kraigg Brathwaite plays it away from his body. The ball goes over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Length ball that keeps coming in from outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite shoulders arms.
Full and on off, shaping in. Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to mid on with soft hands.
Outside off, an easy leave.
Good shot! Length and outside off, this is hit on the up through covers for two.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Bangs it short and on the body, ducked under.
Shorter and on off, this is guided to point.
A little bit of shape away but the line is well outside off, left alone.
Shorter and outside off, this is slapped through covers for one.
Misfield and a run! On off, this is pushed towards cover, the fielder lets it through and a run is taken.
On middle, defended.

OUT! TIMBER! There is the end of a marathon innings from Brathwaite. He falls after facing 11 balls less than 500. A standing ovation for him as he walks off and rightly so. He has led from the front for his side. Also, something special was needed to get rid of him and Leach has provided it. The third new ball does the trick. This starts on off, drifts in, it lands around middle and leg and then spins away sharply. Brathwaite looks to defend but the ball turns enough to go past the outside edge and hit the off pole. Can England make quick work of the lower-order now? Windies still trail by 122.
Howout: b Jack Leach

Commentary: Flatter and on off, extra bounce. Roach does well by taking one hand off the handle and blocking it.
Quicker and outside off, left alone.
Angling into the pads, this is worked in the mid-wicket region for one.
On off, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
On the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side for one.
This one tails back in a touch from around off, blocked.
Back of a length and on off, defended.
Short and outside off, Kemar Roach taps it to the off side.
Spinning away from outside off, Kemar Roach shoulders arms.
Well outside off this time, Kemar Roach leaves it alone.
Tossed up, on off. Kemar Roach keeps it out.
Roach lunges forward and blocks this full ball solidly.
Full and on off, Kemar Roach blocks it off the front foot.
Fuller in length, on off. Joshua Da Silva covers the stumps and drives it to mid on.
Full and on off, Joshua Da Silva defends it out.
Short of a length, on off. Joshua Da Silva pushes it towards covers.
Full and angling in on middle, Joshua Da Silva flicks it to mid-wicket where the fielder dives to his left to stop the ball.
On the pads, Joshua Da Silva tucks it to square leg for a run.
Length ball, outside off. Kemar Roach with an easy leave.
FOUR! Good shot! Short and slower, outside off. Joshua Da Silva gets on top of the bounce and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Quicker this time, on middle. Defended off the back foot.
Flatter ball, outside off. Joshua Da Silva lets it be.
Flatter and quicker, on leg. Joshua Da Silva looks to flick but misses. He gets hit on the pads. England appeal for an LBW but the umpire says no. Going down leg.
Tossed up, outside off. Kept out.
Full and flighted, outside off. Joshua Da Silva defends it out.
Short ball, on middle and leg, Kemar Roach takes his eyes off and lets it pass. The keeper appeals for a catch but it was the sound of the ball brushing his shoulders.
Way down the leg side, left alone.
On a length, on off. Kemar Roach blocks it out watchfully.
Short ball again, on middle. Kemar Roach ducks under it.

OUT! LBW! Chris Woakes with a beautiful inswinger that comes from outside off, Kemar Roach fails to defend it down and gets rapped on the front pad. England appeal and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. West Indies does opt for a review. Nothing on UltraEdge as there is a flat line. Ball Tracking shows that the ball is pitching outside off, the impact is in line and it is umpire's call on wickets hitting. West Indies retain their review but Kemar Roach's short stay comes to an end. West Indies lose their eight wicket and still trail by 115!
Howout: lbw b Chris Woakes

Commentary: Off the mark straightaway! Length ball, outside off. Veerasammy Permaul pushes it through covers for a single. A successful over for Chris Woakes!

Big shout from England but nothing! Tossed up nicely, drifting away, Veerasammy Permaul looks to defend but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge. There might have been be an outside edge there but England do not have any reviews left. Nope, replay shows there wasn't any bat on it. Good decision from the umpire.
Outside off, left alone.
Flatter ball, outside off. Veerasammy Permaul leaves it alone.
Slower through the air, on off. Kept out.
Full and on off, blocked.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball, on middle, angling in. Joshua Da Silva defends it watchfully.
Outside off, on a length, Joshua Da Silva leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Length ball, on middle. Tucked to mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
On a length, outside off. Joshua Da Silva taps it to point.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Clipped to mid-wicket.
Tossed up outside off, Permaul looks to push at it, it goes off the outer half to point.
On off, defended.
Shorter and outside off, this is cut through point for one.
Big turn! This lands on off and then spins away. Joshua looks to block but is beaten.
On off, defended.
Outside off, not played at.
Good length and on off, blocked well.
Almost! Fuller and tailing back in. Permaul looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Shorter and on middle, defended.
Well played in the end! Length and on off, this takes off after landing. Permaul looks to block by taking a hand off the handle but is hit on the glove.
Important runs! Length and on off, Permaul guides it down to third man for two.
A bumper, ducked under. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4!
Length ball, outside off. Joshua Da Silva looks to play at it but the ball bounces a little low.
FOUR! Length ball down leg, Joshua Da Silva tickles it to fine leg for a boundary. 400 up for West Indies!
Length, outside off. Defended to the off side.
Length ball, angling in on middle. Joshua Da Silva gets an inside edge onto the pad. England appeal but the umpire straightaway shakes his head and rightly so.
Fuller in length, on off. Driven back to the bowler.
Short of a length, outside off. Joshua Da Silva stands tall and defends.
Flatter, outside off. Pushed towards point.
Floats it up, on leg. Extra bounce and turn. Veerasammy Permaul gets hit on the pads trying to block and England appeal but nothing from the umpire.
On the pads, Veerasammy Permaul tucks it around the corner for a single.
On off, blocked out.
On middle, kept out.

Nicely floated to angle it across the off stump, Da Silva moves back and across and skews a thick inside edge that goes through his legs and somehow misses the leg pole! Trickled away to short fine leg for one.
On off, this is pushed towards mid-wicket for one.
Shorter and on middle, this is ducked under.
Down the leg side, VP looks to flick but misses.

OUT! THAT WAS PLUMB! It was a review more in hope! Angled into middle, length ball, stays a touch low. Permaul goes back to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal and the finger is raised. It is reviewed but to no avail. Permaul takes a review along with him. England just the one wicket away now from bowling Windies out.
Howout: lbw b Saqib Mahmood

Commentary: Outside off, on a length. Jayden Seales lets it go.
Length ball, on off. Jayden Seales blocks it out with an angled bat.
Tossed up, on middle. Patted back to the bowler.
Short and on off, defended.
Flatter ball, outside off. Left alone.
Loopy ball, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
On off, tapped to the off side.
Loopy ball, on off. Punched back to the bowler. A maiden!
On a length, outside off. Jayden Seales shoulders arms.
Fuller, on off. Jayden Seales defends it out watchfully.
Short of a length, outside off. Jayden Seales lets it be.

Good-length ball, angling in around off. Jayden Seales misses his defence and gets hit on the back pad. England appeal but the umpire says no. The impact was umpire's call there and it was outside off.
Full and down leg, Jayden Seales misses his flick.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
This is clipped to mid-wicket.
Short and on off, punched to mid on.
Loopy ball, on off. Joshua Da Silva defends it off the back foot.
On leg, Joshua Da Silva works it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Full and outside off, Jayden Seales leans and drives it crisply through point for a boundary.
Full and on middle, kept out.
Angled in on middle, this is worked to mid on.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Shorter and on middle, blocked.
Fuller this time and on middle, Seales plays it to covers.
Angled into the pads, this is nudged around the corner for one.
Solid! On a length and around off, kept out.
A huge appeal but turned down. A little too high. This lands outside off and turns back in. Seales looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the back pad.
Tossed up on off, defended.
Flatter and on middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! That is going down leg. It just spun way too much. It lands on middle and then turns in. Seales looks to block but misses to get hit on the pads. A huge shout and the finger is raised. Seales reviews and he survives to fight yet another day.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, defended.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Solid from Seales again. Length and on off, kept out.
Fuller and on off, this is played to covers.
Fuller and on the stumps, kept out.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
On the stumps, blocked.
Full and on off, blocked.
On off, blocked.
Short, on off. Knocked back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on off. Defended.

OUT! LBW! Jack Leach's perseverance pays off. He has bowled almost 70 overs and ends the proceedings for West Indies. He has a big smile on his face. A marathon effort from him. Bowls a flatter ball, on middle and leg, Joshua Da Silva lunges forward to defend but misses. He gets hit on the pads. England appeal and the umpire agrees. Joshua Da Silva reviews it immediately. Nothing on UltraEdge. Ball Tracking shows all three reds. England bowlers can take a breather now. West Indies are all out for 411. England have a lead of 96 runs.
Howout: lbw b Jack Leach

Commentary: Starts off with a short one. Lees looks to pull but gets an under edge onto the pads.
Bangs it short again and outside off, Lees misses out as he chops it to covers.
Better from Roach! Length and on middle, defended.
Back of a length and on middle, kept out.
Angled into middle, this is flicked to mid-wicket.
A maiden to begin with and an effort delivery to end! Shorter and around off, this is guided to point.
England are underway and Crawley is off the pair. On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Shorter and outside off, Lees looks to cut but misses.
Beaten! This lands outside off. Lees okays the for the turn. It goes on the with the arm and he is beaten.
On middle, this one stays low. Lees manages to keep it out.
Beaten again! Just outside off, draws the batter to come forward. Lees again plays for the turn but is beaten as it goes on with the arm.
This time gets bat to ball as he defends this on middle.
Goes past the edge again! Length and outside off, Crawley goes after one he did not need to play. Gets beaten.
On middle, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Lovely delivery! Windies have started off well. Length and it angles in at first. Pitches and moves away. Crawley is beaten as he tries to block.
On middle, blocked.
Angled into the off pole, kept out well.
Shorter and on off, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Leading edge but safe! On middle, this lands and turns a little. Crawley looks to flick but gets a soft leading edge on the off side.
On the pads, this is swept towards fine leg for one.
On off, kept out.
On the stumps, defended.
On middle, Lees is solid in defense.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, not played at again.
On off, defended.
Length ball, worked to mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, ignored.

NOT OUT! An in-angler from Kemar Roach, on middle and leg. Zak Crawley walks across and looks to work it on the leg side but is too late on his shot. He gets pinned on the pads. West Indies appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Zak Crawley takes a review after having a chat with Alex Lees. Nothing on UltraEdge. Wickets missing shows the Ball Tracker. A good review from Zak Crawley and the on-field decision is reversed.
On middle, defended.
Full and outside off, flicked to mid-wicket for a run.
Short and outside off, punched towards covers for one.
Full, on off. Kept out.
Outside off, Alex Lees guides it to third man for a brace.
Flatter, on leg. Alex Lees clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! That's a nice shot! Width offered, outside off. Alex Lees slashes it with hard hands and gets it in the gap. The ball races away to the deep cover fence.
Outside off, on a length. Left alone.
Length ball, outside off. Lees offers no shot.
Short of a length, outside off. Alex Lees punches it to point for a run.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and on off, Zak Crawley drives it to cover.
Floats it up, on leg. Worked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
Full and on off, defended off the front foot.
Short and outside off, Zak Crawley punches it to sweeper cover for one.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
That beats everyone! Spinning in from outside off, Alex Lees looks to work it on the leg side but misses. The ball goes past the stumps and the keeper to fine leg for byes.
Short of a length, on off. Lees taps it to point for a single.
Full and outside off, Zak Crawley lets it go.
Length ball, coming in, on off. Zak Crawley misses his glance and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Length, outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Errs in his length and pitches this one down leg, Zak Crawley tickles it to fine leg for a boundary.
Short of a length, outside off. Zak Crawley offers no shot.
Short and on off, punched back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Lees pushes it to covers.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Floats it up, on off. Defended to mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, Alex Lees looks to drive. The ball skews away off the outside edge to third man for a run.
Outside off, Zak Crawley steers it to deep point and retains the strike.
Slightly shorter and on off, Crawley pulls it to mid on.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Yet another one on a length and around off, this is guided to point.
Well bowled and well played in the end! Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Crawley pulls his bat back at the end.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, this one takes off. Crawley works it down to fine leg for one.
Flatter and on middle, this is worked wide of mid on for one.
Tossed up on off, blocked.
This lands outside off and turns back in sharply. Lees looks to defend but it goes off the inner half on the leg side.
Floats it up on off, defended.
Another one tossed up on off, kept out.
Flatter and on off, Lees is happy to push it to cover.
Pulled away nicely! Shorter and on middle, this is hit through mid-wicket for two.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, this is pushed through covers for one.
Shorter and on middle, this is pulled through mid-wicket for one.
Add two to the total again! Angled into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for a couple.
FOUR! Hit with disdain! Shorter and on middle, this is pulled hard through mid-wicket and it races away.
Fires it on middle, Lees looks to defend but it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and on off, defended.
Two more! Angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, this is pushed to cover for one.
Length ball, outside off. Lees lets it sail through.
Fuller in length, on off. Lees defends it back to the bowler.
Full again, on off. Lees pushes it back to Holder.
On a length, on off. Lees taps it to point.
On off, driven to mid off.
A maiden for Holder! A bit of swing, on off. Alex Lees keeps it out.
Starts off with a flatter ball and on mddle, defended.
Yet again pushes it through, it lands and holds its line. Defended off the back foot.
Tosses it up now and lands it on off, Crawley comes forward and keeps it out.
Three! Shorter and on middle, this is whipped through mid-wicket for three. First runs of the day.
Fuller and on middle, this is played to mid on.

Impact outside off! Signs there of what is going to come, Lees was looking to be positive. He walks across, goes down on one knee and then tries to sweep this from outside off. Misses to get hit on the pads.
A loosener to begin with! This is down the leg side. Zak looks to flick but misses.
On the pads, Crawley works it fine towards fine leg for one.
FOUR! That is a lovely stroke! Lees gets off the mark today with a boundary! Outside off, length, it is slapped through covers for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, Lees pushes it to mid on.
Two more! Fuller and outside off, Lees strokes it through covers for two. Not a good start by Holder. England reach the 50-run mark.
Better from Holder! Ends with a length ball on off, it is played back to the bowler.
Darts it on off, Crawley pushes it to covers.
On off, defended.
That is a good delivery! Tossed up on off, this lands and turns away. Crawley looks to defend, it goes off the outer half to point.
On the pads, this is clipped through square leg for one.

OUT! TAKEN! There is wicket number one for Windies! Lees is the man to walk back. He continues to try to accelerate, which is probably not his game. He looks to play the slog sweep but tries to drag it from outside off. Does not get it right off the middle and hits it straight to deep mid-wicket where Alzarri Joseph takes it.
Howout: c Alzarri Joseph b Veerasammy Permaul

Commentary: Off the mark with two! Edgy runs! On off, slower, Root looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge down to third man for two.
Good length and on off, kept out.
That takes off from a length! England won't mind seeing this! Length and on off, this one takes off after landing. Hits Crawley near the arm as he tries to block.
Another one on a length and around off, kept out.
Shorter and on the body, some steep bounce again. Crawley looks to fend it away but it hits the glove and goes on the leg side.
Two again! Angled into the pads, Crawley works it through square leg and takes two.
Angled into the pads again, Crawley looks to nudge it on the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Flatter and on off, this is played to point.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for one.
On off, this is defended.
The sweep is out, it is played through square leg for one.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on middle, ZC looks to push at it, it goes off the inner half to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, outside off. Joe Root defends it out.
Back of a length, on off. Joe Root taps it to point.
Length ball, on off. Root nudges it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, on off. Joe Root gets behind the line and pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length again, on off. Zak Crawley blocks it from the crease.
FOUR! Short ball, on off. Zak Crawley mistimes his pull. It goes off the top edge over the keeper's head for a boundary.
FOUR! Up and over! Joe Root advances down the track and takes the ball on full, smacks it over mid on for a boundary. Good intent by England captain!

OUT! CAUGHT! England are going for the push but they need to be careful here. Can't keep losing wickets. Joe Root departs as well. West Indies will be pleased with this. Loopy ball from Veerasammy Permaul, on middle. Joe Root strides forward and goes for the sweep. Comes off the bottom half of the bat to deep mid-wicket where John Campbell takes a simple catch. Dan Lawrence walks out to bat.
Howout: c John Campbell b Veerasammy Permaul

Commentary: Flatter and quicker, on middle. Zak Crawley punches it to the off side.
Short, on middle. Zak Crawley works it through mid-wicket for a brace.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
On the pads, Zak Crawley turns it to square leg for a single.
Short ball down leg, Zak Crawley looks to pull but misses.
FOUR! Great shot! Overpitched, outside off. Zak Crawley drives it on the up and creams it through covers. Sublime stroke and gets a boundary for that.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another batsman departs trying to go big. This time it's Zak Crawley. England lose their third wicket. Alzarri Joseph strikes back immediately. Bowls it short now, on middle. Zak Crawley goes for the pull. It comes off the splice of the bat to wide of deep square leg. Jayden Seales sprints in from fine leg and takes it with both hands. Takes it inches above the ground. Magnificent catch from him! England lead by 170 runs!
Howout: c Jayden Seales b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Short of a length, outside off. Dan Lawrence dabs it down to third man for a single.
Length ball, on leg. Stokes turns it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on off. Ben Stokes taps it to point for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Stokes lets it be.
Outside off, on a length. Stokes carves it but straight to covers.
Short of a length, on off. Stokes defends it out.
Length, outside off. Ben Stokes has a slash at it but misses.
Full and outside off, Ben Stokes reaches out for it and slices it to backward point for a single.
Short ball, on middle. Dan Lawrence shuffles across and pulls it to fine leg for one.
Length ball, on off. Dan Lawrence works it softly through mid-wicket for a single.
Nicely played! Short of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes guides it nicely past the second slip fielder to third man for a single.
That one just took off! Length ball, outside off, shoot up after landing. Dan Lawrence looks to defend but is taken aback by the bounce. It goes well over his blade.
On a length, outside off. Dan Lawrence steers it to deep backward point for a run.
On the pads, Stokes works it through mid-wicket and crosses ends.
Short ball, on middle. Dan Lawrence steps out and tries to pull but the ball goes off the undeer edge and rolls back just past the stumps.
WIDE! That is very, very wide outside off, almost off the wicket. Left alone. Wided.
FOUR! Up and over! That has been hit with brute force! Shorter and on off, Stokes slaps it over covers for a boundary.

SIX! That is the power of Stokes! He did not get that off the middle but still goes over the fence. Shuffles across and Roach bowls it on middle, this is heaved over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Now a run! Fuller and outside off, Stokes looks to go for it but it goes off the inside edge down to fine leg for one. No ball too.
Fuller and on middle, this is worked down to long on for one. He does the right thing by giving Stokes the strike.
Bangs it short and outside off, this is slapped through covers, there is protection in the deep so only one.
Outside off, Dan Lawrence guides it through point for one more.
Stokes retains strike! End of a really good over for England! Fuller and on off, this is hit down towards long off for one.
On the body, this is pushed down to long on for one more. 100 up for England.

SIX! That has been hit with disdain! Outstanding shot! Shorter and on off, this is heaved over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie. The lead is now over 200. Probably another 50 runs before we see the declaration.
Shorter and on off, this is guided to point.
Fuller and outside off, Dan Lawrence swings really hard, it goes off the inner half back to the bowler.
Another dot! On off, Lawrence guides it to point.
On a length and on off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Very full and outside off, this is hit down to long off for one more.
Lawrence shuffles across, he gets a full toss on middle, it is worked wide of long on. He wants two but has to settle for one.
Outside off, it is jammed out to point.

OUT! TAKEN! There was just the one man close-in on the off side and Stokes has picked him out perfectly. This is full and outside off, Stokes looks to hit it hard but straight to Kraigg Brathwaite at covers. Windies continue to chip away at the wickets.
Howout: c Kraigg Brathwaite b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Fuller and on middle, this is worked to mid on.
Outside off, fuller, this is hit through covers for one.
A yorker now on middle, this is jammed out to covers.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
On the fuller side, this is pushed down to long on for a single.
Shorter and outside off, Bairstow looks to pull it across the line but misses.
Fuller and outside off, Jonny Bairstow opens the face of the bat and guides it through point for one. They took the first one hard but the fielder was quick to the ball so only one.
Shorter and on middle, this is pulled through square leg for one.
A yorker now on middle, this is jammed back to the bowler.
Another yorker on middle, this is jammed back to the bowler.
Two more! On off, this is driven through covers for two.
Shorter and on middle, this is pulled but to mid-wicket.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
On off, this is hit down to long off for one.
This is steered down to third man for a single.
Right into the blockhole, squeezed to backward point.
A full toss, outside off. Driven to sweeper cover for a run.
FOUR! Lucky! Around off, Jonny Bairstow looks to squeeze it through the off side but it goes off the inside edge down to the fine leg fence.
A single to end! Outside off, this is guided down to third man for one.
Shorter and on middle, this is pulled through square leg for one.
Lawrence comes down the track and pushes it down to long on for one.
Good length and on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
That one stays low! On middle, this one does not bounce a lot. Jonny Bairstow looks to flick but gets a soft leading edge back to the bowler.
A yorker now, this is jammed out to covers for one more.
FOUR! That is lovely placement! A full toss outside off, this is carved past point and into the fence.
SIX! That is trademark Bairstow! On the pads, he whips it well over the square leg fence for a biggie.
SIX! Over the fence! Fuller and on middle, this is lofted over the bowler's head and it goes all the way. Consecutive biggies, this one better than the last.
Just the one! Outside off, this is hit towards sweeper cover for one.
Slower one outside off, this is hit through covers for one.
Well wide outside off, left alone. Jonny Bairstow wanted a wide but not given.
Just the one again! On off, this is cut through point for a single. A really good over for England.
Shorter and just outside off, not a lot of room on offer and also extra bounce. Bairstow looks to cut but is beaten.
Slower and on the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Short of a length, on off. Dan Lawrence works it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Full and down leg, Jonny Bairstow tries to sweep it but misses.
Full and on off, Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
Good running! On a length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow glances it to deep square leg for a brace.
SIX! Lovely hitting! In the slot, outside off. Dan Lawrence stands tall and tonks it over long off for a biggie.
A yorker now on off, Dan Lawrence squeezes it out to long off for a run.
Fullish, outside off. Jonny Bairstow swipes it hard to deep mid-wicket for a run. 50-run partnership between these two as well.
A full toss, outside off. Dan Lawrence steers it to deep point for one.

OUT! CAUGHT! Good take from Kemar Roach in the deep and Jonny Bairstow has to walk back. Jayden Seales gets his man. Full and outside off, Jonny Bairstow couldn't quite get underneath it. He heaves it to long off where Kemar Roach charges ahead and takes a good sharp low catch. Half the side back in the hut and England has a lead of 257! Maybe they will look to add another 50 before we see a declaration?
Howout: c Kemar Roach b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Fuller in length, outside off. Dan Lawrence pushes it to long on for a single.
A slow yorker, on middle. Dan Lawrence nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
Short of a length, on off. Ben Foakes blocks it out.
Fullish, on off. Worked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
This is pushed through covers for a single.
On a length, on middle. Ben Foakes tucks it to square leg and crosses ends.
Full and on leg, Dan Lawrence pushes it to mid off for a run.
Full and on off, Dan Lawrence smashes it to long off but doesn't take a single. Maybe this is the last over before we see a declaration.
Fullish, outside off. Dan Lawrence reaches out and squeezes it to the off side.

OUT! CAUGHT! Dan Lawrence walks back for a well-made 41. This is full again, outside off. Dan Lawrence walks across and loses his balance. He still throws the kitchen sink at it and smashes it to long on. Didn't hit it off the middle and Alzarri Joseph takes a simple catch. No signs of declaration yet as Chris Woakes walks out to bat.
Howout: c Alzarri Joseph b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Full and outside off, Ben Foakes looks to drive. The ball goes off the inside edge to fine leg for a single.
Short ball, on middle. Woakes pulls it to fine leg and gets off the mark with a single.
Full and outside off, Ben Foakes drives it to long off for a single.
Short ball, on middle. Ben Foakes pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short of a length now, on off. Chris Woakes works it nicely to deep mid-wicket for a single.
On middle, nudged to square leg for a run.
Fuller in length, on off. Woakes digs it out to point and rotates the strike.
On a length, on middle. Ben Foakes clips it to deep square leg for a run.
Fuller, on off. Driven to long off for a single.
Short ball, on middle. Chris Woakes pulls it along the carpet to deep square leg for just a single.
Length ball, well outside off. Ben Foakes tries to reach out but misses.
Full and on off, eased down to long off for a single.
Wide outside off, Woakes chases it and works it to cover for a single.
Again wide outside off, Ben Foakes pushes it to sweeper cover for one.
Full and on middle, Chris Woakes chips it to long on for a single.
Full and on off, Chris Woakes pushes it to long on. Calls for the second and gets it easily.
A very slow yorker, wide outside off. Ben Foakes waits for it and pushes it towards covers for a run.
Short of a length, outside off. Chris Woakes chops it back to the keeper.
Short of a length, on middle. Chris Woakes hops and tucks it to mid-wicket. He crosses ends.
Short ball, on middle. Pulled to deep square leg for a single.
Extra bounce straightaway! Length ball, on middle, the ball shoots up. Kraigg Brathwaite is taken aback and defends it one-handed. The ball pops up and falls over short leg.
Good-length ball, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Fuller this time, on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite tickles it to deep square leg for a single. He is off the mark.
On a good length, outside off. John Campbell with a good front foot block.
Short of a length, on off. John Campbell hops and defends it out.
Length ball, wide outside off. John Campbell lets it go.
Shaping it away from outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite shoulders arms.
Good length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite covers the line and keeps it out.
Short ball that stays quite low. Kraigg Brathwaite ducks under it.
Good length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite cuts it to backward point.
Well bowled! Good-length ball, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the front foot. A maiden for Matthew Fisher!
Length ball, on off. John Campbell stands tall and defends it onto the pitch.
Little fuller this time, outside off. John Campbell pushes it to point.

FOUR! Edgy runs! Full and outside off, John Campbell leans and looks to drive. The ball takes the outside edge and flies past gully. The ball races away to the fence. That's exactly what Woakes was setting him up for but flies wide of gully to his left.
Full and outside off, kept out.
Length ball, nips away from outside off. John Campbell leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, closer to the fourth stump channel. John Campbell decides to leave again.
Nice punch! Length ball, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite punches it through covers. Gets three runs for it.
Length ball on leg, John Campbell glances it to fine leg for a run.
Full and on off, blocked out to the off side by Kraigg Brathwaite.
Good length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite covers the line and knocks it back to the bowler.
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite is very solid in his defence.
Back of a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite hops and defends.
Short ball, on off. John Campbell rides the bounce and pulls it to deep mid-wicket. Good intent from him and he gets two runs.
Good-length ball, on middle. Defended back to the bowler.
Full and shaping away outside off, John Campbell lets it sail through.
Shaping away from outside off, on a good length, John Campbell shoulders arms.
Goes full now, on off. Campbell blocks it out.
Nicely clipped! Full and on the pads, John Campbell clips it to deep mid-wicket. Gets three runs before the fielder cuts it off near the ropes.
Starts with a shorter delivery that turns into the batter. John Campbell pulls it to backward square leg.

An appeal but the umpire is not interested. Pitches outside off and turns into Campbell. He looks to sweep it but misses and the ball hits his pads. There is an huge appeal but the umpire denies the call.
Shorter on middle. Campbell pulls it to backward square leg again.
A flatter delivery on off. Campbell defends it out.
Slightly shorter on middle. Campbell pulls it to square leg.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jack Leach strikes in his first over and he is once again showing his worth. Great review taken by England. Fantastic start by Jack Leach.  Pitches this around off and it turns into Campbell sharply again. He looks to defend off the front foot but gets the inside edge onto his pads and the ball loops in the air towards short leg. Lees there takes a fine catch and England appeal. However, the umpire is not interested and England review. The replays roll in and the UltraEdgte shows that there is glove involved there and England have an early breakthrough here.
Howout: c Alex Lees b Jack Leach

Commentary: An inswinger, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it on the leg side.
Fuller, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it through covers for a single.

An appeal again but England decide to not take a review this time. On a length and angling into leg. Brooks looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits his pads and goes towards fine leg and the batters run a leg bye. There is an appeal meanwhile but it is going down leg.
On a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the leg side.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone watchfully.
Tad fuller this time on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it back to the bowler.
Quicker and flatter on off. Brooks gets well forward and blocks it.

FOUR! Lovely delivery again but this time a boundary for Brooks and he gets off the mark. This is slower in the air, on off. Brooks stride forward to defend. The ball catches the outside edge of his blade and goes past first slip for a boundary.
Beaten! Quicker around off. Brooks looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
Fuller on off. Brooks defends it off the front foot.
Very full again, on off. Brooks defends it back to the bowler.
Another quicker and fuller delivery on off. Brook drives it to mid off.
Goes short and wide outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to cut but misses as the ball seams away a bit.
A full toss outside off at 128 kph. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it through covers for a couple.
Back of a length, around off at 131 kph. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
Back of a length, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it to covers for a single.
A good-length delivery on off at 135 kph. Brooks blocks it solidly onto the turf.

OUT! CAUGHT! Second wicket down now and West Indies are in early trouble. Great presence of mind shown by the English skipper, Root. Back of a length, outside off. Brooks looks to punch it towards covers. However, he gets a thick outside edge to second slip. Zak Crawley there fails to pouch it in the first attempt and the ball goes behind him. He then tries to catch it with his right hand in the second attempt but fails and the ball pops up in the air. Root at first slip is aware and takes a catch moving to his right, Brilliant stuff from the English skipper. It was also the first catch in the slip cordon of this Test.
Howout: c Joe Root b Saqib Mahmood

Commentary: Tossed up, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it through covers for a couple.
Flatter ball, full and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it to the off side.
A fuller delivery, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it through covers for a couple.
A flatter delivery, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
FOUR! Lovely shot this time. It is quicker and fuller on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it past mid on for a boundary.
Quicker and flatter on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the off side.
Fuller, on off. Bonner drives it straight to cover.
On a length, on middle. Nkrumah Bonner hops and defends it on the leg side.
Outside off, on a length, shaping away. Nkrumah Bonner leaves it untouched.
Nicely played! Full and outside off, Nkrumah Bonner leans onto that and drives it crisply through covers for three runs.
Length ball, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it to extra cover for a single.
On a length, on leg. Nkrumah Bonner fends it away on the leg side.
Full and on leg, Kraigg Brathwaite clears his front leg and pushes it to mid on.
Tossed up, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite strides forward and blocks.
FOUR! What a shot! Straight as it could be! Loopy ball, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite uses his feet and smashes it straight as an arrow to get a boundary. Aggressive hitting from the Windies skipper.
Floats it up, on off. Blocked out.
Outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite guides it to third man. Good chase for the fielder from slip and he keeps it down to two.
Kept low this time, short on the outside off, turning away as Brathwaite gets forward to leave that one alone.

OUT!  EDGED AND TAKEN! Number three down and West Indies are now in serious trouble here. Saqib Mahmood delivering the goods. The extra bounce causes problems. Length and on off, this lands and takes off. Bonner looks to defend. It goes off the outside edge to the Root at first slip.
Howout: c Joe Root b Saqib Mahmood

Commentary: Length again and on off, kept out. Good stuff from Mahmood, testing stuff.
Back of a length this time and on off, Blackwood pushes it to covers.
Nicely played! Shorter and on middle, Blackwood gets on top of the bounce and defends.
Back of a length and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Another back of a length ball and on off, JB plays it to cover.
On middle, kept out.
Tossed up on middle, defended.
Another one tossed up and on off, kept out.
Fuller and on middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
On the stumps, kept out.
Attacks the stumps again. It is defended.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Loose! This is quite wide outside off, Blackwood has a poke at it but is beaten. Not sure if the edge would have carried as that stayed low.
Back of a length and on off, kept out.
Shorter and on middle, this is nudged to mid-wicket.
Well bowled! Shorter and on off, gets big on the batter. Blackwood does well to get on top of the bounce and guide it to gully.
Another shorter in length ball. Kept out.
Slower in the air, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite gets well forward and defends it.
Quicker and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone watchfully.
Fuller on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it towards the non-striker. The ball hits his blade and goes towards mid off.
Slower in the air, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the off side.
Goes slightly short around off. Kraigg Brathwaite goes deep in his crease and cuts it through point for a couple.
Quicker on off. Kraigg Brathwaite gets well forward and blocks it out.
On a length, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood works it to mid-wicket. The fielder misfields and a single is taken.
On a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite works it to mid-wicket.
Lands on a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Serves on a length again, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it to right of mid off.
Back of a length, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and defends it out.

FOUR! Edged but a boundary for the Windies skipper! Lands on a length, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite goes for a drive away from his body. The ball catches the outside edge of his blade and the ball goes through backward point for a boundary.
A fuller delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it out.
Goes flatter and quicker on middle. Jermaine Blackwood gets a good stride forward and defends it.
Darted on middle and leg. Jermaine Blackwood works it towards the deep backward square leg region. The batters run three. Good running.
Slower in the air, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Again, on the off stump line and fuller. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it watchfully off the front foot.
Quicker and flatter on off. Kraigg Brathwaite with a solid front foot defence again.
Slower in the air, around off. Jermaine Blackwood gets well forward and blocks it.
On middle and turning down the leg side. Jermaine Blackwood looks to work it away but misses.

A huge appeal but it is way too high! On middle and turning into the batter with some good bounce. Jermaine Blackwood looks to defend it off the back foot but the ball hits him high on the pad. There is an appeal but the umpire is not interested.
A flatter delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it out.
Short and wide outside off. Jermaine Blackwood cuts it to point.
A Slightly shorter delivery on middle and leg. Jermaine Blackwood looks to work it towards the leg side. He gets the inside edge onto the pads and the ball falls short of the keeper to his right.
Lands on a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite works it past mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length, around off. Jermaine Blackwood rides the bounce and punches it to covers.
NO BALL! Ben Stokes has overstepped! Back of a length, arounJermaine Blackwood punches this off the back foot towards the off side.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone.
Lands on a length, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood works it right of short leg. He stops it as the ball falls short of him.
On the shorter side, around off. Jermaine Blackwood defends it towards the off side.
In that channel around off, on a good length. Jermaine Blackwood decides to leave it alone.
A flatter delivery on middle and slightly shorter. Kraigg Brathwaite works it to fine leg for a single.
Around off and again on the shorter side. Jermaine Blackwood punches it to covers.
Quicker on middle. Jermaine Blackwood goes deep in his crease and pushes it towards the leg side.
On middle and leg. Jermaine Blackwood works it towards fine leg.

An appeal but turn down by the umpire! On middle and turning into the batter with some extra bounce. Jermaine Blackwood looks to work it towards the leg side but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal. It is too high and the umpire is not interested.
Flatter on off. Jermaine Blackwood punches it to covers.
Back of a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite goes back and defends it.
Serves it on a length, around off and it keeps a bit low. Kraigg Brathwaite defends but gets the outside edge of his blade to gully.
Lands on a length again, maybe a tad fuller. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it to mid off.
On a good length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Hits the length again, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it watchfully.
Stokes goes wide of his crease and angles it on off, on the shorter side. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and blocks it out.
Slower in the air, around off. It turns away sharply and beats the outside edge of Jermaine Blackwood's blade as he looks to defend.
A flatter delivery, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone.
On the shorter side, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood cuts it through point for a couple.
Goes slightly short on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it out.
Quicker and flatter on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it off the back foot.
Beats him this time! Lands it just short of full-length, around off. Jermaine Blackwood presses forward to defend but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade as it turns away sharply.
Short of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Extra bounce! Length ball, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite is surprised by the bounce and takes a blow on the gloves.
Angled in, full and on off. Kraigg Brathwaite gets behind to block.
Length ball, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite shoulders arms.
Back of a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite hops and taps it to the off side.
Fuller, on off. Defended back to the bowler. A maiden!
Quicker, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood keeps it out.
Tossed up, on off. Jermaine Blackwood prods and blocks.
Flatter, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Short and outside off, extra bounce as well. Jermaine Blackwood lets it go.
Tossed up, on middle. Pushed to mid on.
Short and slower, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood rocks back and cuts it to sweeper cover for a brace.
Short ball, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite sits under it.
Short of a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite goes on the back foot and drops it on the off side.
Good length, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite watches the ball closely and lets it sail through. A good leave!
This is tucked to mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Ripper! Back of a length into Blackwood on the fourth stump line, Jermaine Blackwood gets forward as he decides to drop his bat down at the last second. Beats the outside edge to the keeper.
Full and on middle, defended.
Loopy ball, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it easily.
Full again, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite keeps it out.
Flatter, on leg. Kraigg Brathwaite stays solid in his defence.
Attacking the stumps, Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out off the front foot.
Full and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it to the off side.
Length ball down leg, Jermaine Blackwood looks to whip it away but misses.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball, on middle. Nudged to mid-wicket for a single.
On a good length, on off. Defended off the front foot.
Length ball, on off, keeps low as well. Kraigg Brathwaite does well to block it out.
Full and on off, pushed towards covers.
Short and on off, Jermaine Blackwood works it to mid-wicket.
Full and drifting on the pads, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it to the vacant deep square leg region and gets three.
Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
Full and on off, defended out.
On middle, kept out.
Full and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it easily.
Floats it up, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood goes back and works it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Short and on off, Jermaine Blackwood stays back and defends.
On the pads, clipped to square leg.
Full and outside off, Jermaine Blackwood strides forward and defends.

Short and on middle and leg, Jermaine Blackwood hangs back and looks to work it on the leg side. The ball keeps very low and he gets an inside edge onto the pads. England appeal for an LBW but the umpire says no. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 5!
Finds the edge straightaway! Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Brathwaite looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge. Well short of gully.
A little bit of extra bounce this time and it is pushed through covers for one. First run of the session.
Back of a length and on middle, defended.
Angled into middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Yet another one on the pads, Blackwood works it to mid-wicket.
Shorter in length and outside off, Blackwood pushes it to covers.
Starts off with one down the leg side. Brathwaite looks to flick but misses.
On the pads again, Brathwaite lets it be.
Flatter and on the leg pole. This is worked to mid-wicket.
A huge appeal but turned down. Probably going down leg. Tossed up on middle, Brathwaite swings, the ball lands and tune back in. Hits him on the pads. An appeal but turned down.
Three! This is more safe and controlled! Shorter and outside off, this is played past point for three.
Tossed up on off, Dan plays it back to the bowler.
A single! Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Back of a length and on off, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Back of a length again and on off, JB keeps it out.
On middle, this is pushed to mid on.
On the shorter side and on off, Blackwood stays back and blocks.
Mahmood felt there was an edge but nothing from anyone else! Shorter and outside off, Blackwood looks to push at it but is beaten.
Almost! That is a lovely delivery. It is tossed up outside off, it lands in the rough. Turns back in. Brathwaite looks to drive but it goes off the inside edge past short leg for one.
Another one tossed up and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Sharp turn! This lands outside off and spins back in. Blackwood looks to flick but misses to get hit on the body.
Another one tossed up on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Flatter and on middle, Blackwood works it to mid-wicket.
On middle, this is worked with the turn to square leg. A testing over by Lawrence.
Goos length and on off, this is pushed back to the bowler. No ball signaled as Saqib has overstepped.
Shorter and on the body, this is pulled down to fine leg for one.
Back of a length and on middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Two! Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for a couple.
Another back of a length ball on off, Blackwood pushes it to covers.
Three more! Shorter and on off, Blackwood pushes it down past mid off for three.
Angled into middle, this is worked to mid on.
FOUR! Sliced away! Outside off, fuller. Blackwood goes after it, it slices off the bat, no one at point and a boundary results.
FOUR! Hit hard! Fuller and outside off, this is drilled through covers for a boundary.
Flatter and outside off, left alone.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to square leg.
Another loud appeal but it is going down leg. On the pads, Blackwood leaves it alone. It hits the pad.
Nicely bowled! Slows it up and lands it on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Fractionally short and outside off, this is played through point for two.
Gives it air this time and lands it on off, blocked.
Yet another one on the shorter side and outside off, it is played through point for one. Fifty run stand up and the two continue to do well for their side. Still some way to go.
On middle, defended.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! The stand, which was frustrating England has been breached. Leach is the one to do the job and it is game on now. 6 more wickets to be taken with over 25 overs left. Lovely nut. It lands on middle and then spins away. Blackwood looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge to Bairstow who is in the gully region but very, very close. He has his helmet and is on his knees. It goes straight to him and he makes no mistake.
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Jack Leach

Commentary: Off the outer half again! Tossed up on off, Holder looks to defend but this one turns away. It goes off the outer half to point.
Tossed up on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle again, this is flicked to mid-wicket again.
Flatter and on the pads, Brathwaite plays it on the leg side again.
That is a harmless ball! Way down the leg side. Left alone. The keeper does not collect it too but no run taken.
That is a beauty! Brathwaite though should have played ahead. He goes back to a tossed up ball. He tries to block but does so inside the line. The ball beats the outside edge.
On middle, it is flicked to mid-wicket.
On middle, kept out.
Ohhh! Tossed up again and on off, Holder tries to defend but this turns away, takes the outer half, falls safe on the off side.
On off, this is defended.
Pushes this one through, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on middle, Holder negotiates it well.
Another over goes by! On middle, this is kept out well.
Almost a yorker outside off, this is jammed out to covers.
Loopy ball on off, it is pushed to covers.
Loud shout but not given! Too high. Flatter and outside off, this one turns back in. Brathwaite fails to put bat on ball and gets hit high on the pads.
Slows it up and floats it on off. Defended.
Shorter and outside off, this is guided towards third man for two.
Flatter and on middle, Brathwaite goes back and gets his bat down in time.
On middle, defended.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a brilliant catch by Lawrence! You need to hang onto the half chances in such games and Lawrence has done so. The big wicket is Holder has been taken. Leach is the one yet again. That though is a loose stroke from Holder. It is short and outside off. Turns away. Holder pushes at it away from the body. He hits it uppishly towards cover. Dan dives to his left and takes it brilliantly. Five more wickets needed. Still a lot of time left in this game.
Howout: c Dan Lawrence b Jack Leach
